WEBVTT

1
00:00:18.045 --> 00:00:18.885
Are we on?

2
00:00:24.742 --> 00:00:25.938
Hello.

3
00:00:26.863 --> 00:00:29.464
When? Thank you.

4
00:00:30.544 --> 00:00:32.662
Yes. I'll tell him.

5
00:00:37.677 --> 00:00:38.336
Sir.

6
00:00:41.619 --> 00:00:42.340
He's gone.

7
00:00:47.601 --> 00:00:49.689
Contact family members…

8
00:00:49.712 --> 00:00:51.643
the various corporate boards…

9
00:00:51.723 --> 00:00:55.959
and business interests.

10
00:00:56.173 --> 00:00:56.741
Yes. sir.

11
00:00:58.938 --> 00:01:01.551
Sir. I...

12
00:01:01.631 --> 00:01:04.526
I am so sorry
for your loss.

13
00:01:12.885 --> 00:01:16.676
Am I speakin'
to a Theophilus Hamilton of Birmingham?

14
00:01:16.753 --> 00:01:18.918
Sir? Yes. sir. This is he.

15
00:01:18.996 --> 00:01:21.855
Name's Howard Stevens.
You can call me Red.

16
00:01:21.897 --> 00:01:24.962
I need a lawyer for a few
business ideas I have…

17
00:01:25.004 --> 00:01:27.169
a few still
in the dream stage.

18
00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:44.877
Though the skies may weep…

19
00:01:44.955 --> 00:01:48.551
the Bible assures us thatprecious in the sight
of the Lord… is the death of his saints.

20
00:01:50.859 --> 00:01:54.256
I wonder who the old man
negotiated with for the rain.

21
00:01:54.296 --> 00:01:56.764
Well. it's a sure bet
he's laughin'…

22
00:01:56.832 --> 00:01:58.823
watchin' us get soaked.

23
00:01:59.835 --> 00:02:02.464
Yeah. well.
now it's his turn.

24
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:05.234
There's not a person here
whose life. in some way…

25
00:02:05.274 --> 00:02:08.608
has not been touched
by Howard “Red” Stevens.

26
00:02:09.879 --> 00:02:12.278
Red often quoted
Malcolm Muggeridge…

27
00:02:12.348 --> 00:02:15.579
saying that. “Every happening.
great or small…

28
00:02:15.651 --> 00:02:19.280
”is a parable by which
God speaks to us…

29
00:02:19.355 --> 00:02:22.620
and the art of life
is to get the message.”

30
00:02:24.527 --> 00:02:29.806
May the message of Red Stevens
continue in the hearts of those he leaves behind.

31
00:02:30.934 --> 00:02:34.432
- What are you doing? You're gonna get all wet.
- Bill.

32
00:02:38.407 --> 00:02:43.027
Even though Dad moved his corporate offices
from Texas many years ago…

33
00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.138
for tax reasons…

34
00:02:46.215 --> 00:02:49.846
he always said he wanted
to be buried under Texas soil.

35
00:03:12.442 --> 00:03:14.932
Is that him?

36
00:03:16.413 --> 00:03:18.347
That's him.

37
00:03:31.794 --> 00:03:35.026
Mom.

38
00:03:35.098 --> 00:03:38.555
- You're late.
- For what?

39
00:03:45.174 --> 00:03:47.301
Give me some of that!

40
00:03:47.376 --> 00:03:49.367
Settle down over there.

41
00:03:59.555 --> 00:04:01.785
Good morning.

42
00:04:01.857 --> 00:04:04.894
Before we start.
I'd like to say how much Red…

43
00:04:05.962 --> 00:04:07.952
meant to me personally.

44
00:04:09.198 --> 00:04:13.157
As you know. we started out
as business partners…

45
00:04:15.404 --> 00:04:19.273
and we ended up
as friends.

46
00:04:20.543 --> 00:04:23.670
I am deeply grieved
by his passing.

47
00:04:23.746 --> 00:04:25.942
Yes. well. that's very nice.

48
00:04:26.015 --> 00:04:28.006
Now. may we proceed?

49
00:04:35.758 --> 00:04:39.250
Red's will
is in his own words…

50
00:04:39.328 --> 00:04:43.493
still. every bit
as legal and binding...

51
00:04:43.566 --> 00:04:46.295
Blah. blah. blah.

52
00:04:47.736 --> 00:04:50.831
“And. so.
my eldest son. Bill…

53
00:04:52.108 --> 00:04:56.305
I leave my company.
Panhandle Oil and Gas.”

54
00:04:56.378 --> 00:04:59.974
Currently worth $600 million.

55
00:05:00.049 --> 00:05:04.947
“However. Bill. since you had
zero interest in my company while I was alive…

56
00:05:04.987 --> 00:05:08.616
”I don't imagine that will
change much after my death.

57
00:05:08.690 --> 00:05:10.820
Therefore. the board
will maintain control.”

58
00:05:10.860 --> 00:05:15.956
Excuse me. but my client would like
to explore all of his options.

59
00:05:16.031 --> 00:05:18.693
Your client
has no more options.

60
00:05:18.767 --> 00:05:20.829
One of those instructions
Mr Hamilton skipped over…

61
00:05:20.869 --> 00:05:24.933
is Red's desire that each of you vacate
after receiving your portion of the estate.

62
00:05:24.973 --> 00:05:28.571
- As in. leave the room.
- What the... She can't talk to me like that.

63
00:05:28.611 --> 00:05:33.343
- Well. do something.
- You can go now. Mr Stevens.

64
00:05:33.415 --> 00:05:36.379
- What... All right. Fine. Fine.
- We should really go.

65
00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:38.750
I have never been so humiliated.

66
00:05:38.821 --> 00:05:41.183
Did you see that old man
talking' to me that way?

67
00:05:41.223 --> 00:05:44.919
And you guys just sat there
and said absolutely nothin'.

68
00:05:46.762 --> 00:05:49.390
That's it?

69
00:05:50.866 --> 00:05:54.768
- A cow farm?
- A 10.000-acre cow farm.

70
00:05:58.508 --> 00:06:01.840
Well. what's that worth anyway?

71
00:06:04.112 --> 00:06:06.546
Ruth. come on.
Come here.

72
00:06:06.615 --> 00:06:09.550
What exactly do we get?

73
00:06:09.618 --> 00:06:12.348
A place for you
to take your mistress.

74
00:06:12.421 --> 00:06:15.050
Come on. Ruth.
Let me explain.

75
00:06:15.124 --> 00:06:17.886
- I want to see everything! Full disclosure.
- Come on. Jack. Let's go.

76
00:06:17.926 --> 00:06:20.323
- Good day. Mr Stevens.
- You said you had a strategy!

77
00:06:20.363 --> 00:06:23.059
- This is a long way from over.
- You said it was a slam dunk!

78
00:06:23.099 --> 00:06:27.694
- “To Sarah. widow of my late son.
Jay Howard Stevens…

79
00:06:27.769 --> 00:06:30.739
”I am truly sorry
for the events of the past.

80
00:06:30.806 --> 00:06:35.368
”Please know that Jay‘s death
represents the greatest tragedy…

81
00:06:35.444 --> 00:06:37.572
”I have ever experienced.

82
00:06:37.647 --> 00:06:42.310
”I leave you control of my Myers Park estate
where you now reside…

83
00:06:42.384 --> 00:06:47.084
”and a managed trust for expenses as long as you live.”
- There we go.

84
00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:51.019
“Since your choice
of male companionship is vast and varied…

85
00:06:51.059 --> 00:06:56.273
the deed and title for the house
will remain under the control of my trustees.”

86
00:06:58.367 --> 00:07:01.462
- Good day. Mr Hamilton.
- Good day.

87
00:07:03.739 --> 00:07:08.370
It's amazing just how far
the fruit can fall from the tree.

88
00:07:08.444 --> 00:07:10.571
And still roll
a great distance.

89
00:07:10.813 --> 00:07:14.441
Nice of you to show up.

90
00:07:14.516 --> 00:07:16.541
You're in time for nothin'.

91
00:07:16.618 --> 00:07:18.553
Let's go.

92
00:07:24.094 --> 00:07:26.358
Jason.

93
00:07:26.430 --> 00:07:29.332
How do you know
my name?

94
00:07:29.401 --> 00:07:32.864
It's my business to know everyone
named in your grandfather's will.

95
00:07:32.904 --> 00:07:35.934
Let's cut the b.s.. 'cause
I know what he left me... nothing.

96
00:07:35.974 --> 00:07:38.548
Walk away... you'll never know.
will you?

97
00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:50.850
Jason?

98
00:08:01.902 --> 00:08:03.962
So. what's in the box?

99
00:08:04.038 --> 00:08:06.700
Your inheritance.

100
00:08:08.076 --> 00:08:10.068
Have a seat.

101
00:08:12.547 --> 00:08:17.112
Does the box or the seal appear to have been
tampered with in any way?

102
00:08:17.152 --> 00:08:19.143
No.

103
00:08:21.123 --> 00:08:23.591
Then therefore
witness this day…

104
00:08:25.661 --> 00:08:29.428
that I am
breaking the seal…

105
00:08:29.499 --> 00:08:32.697
affixed in my presence
by Red himself.

106
00:08:43.714 --> 00:08:47.582
- Miss Hastings.
- Yes. sir.

107
00:08:53.091 --> 00:08:55.617
- Are we on?
- Yes. we are.

108
00:08:55.695 --> 00:08:58.755
Mmm. Well. then.
If you're watching this…

109
00:08:58.831 --> 00:09:00.823
I must be dead.

110
00:09:00.901 --> 00:09:02.892
That's a strange concept.

111
00:09:02.970 --> 00:09:05.234
How was my funeral?
Well attended?

112
00:09:05.305 --> 00:09:07.773
I hope it rained.

113
00:09:07.841 --> 00:09:10.332
Hamilton. Miss Hastings…

114
00:09:10.411 --> 00:09:13.315
I hope you're having
a better day than I am.

115
00:09:13.347 --> 00:09:16.449
If you've just been
with my family. I doubt it.

116
00:09:17.518 --> 00:09:20.852
Jason. I made a lot
Of mistakes with our family…

117
00:09:20.922 --> 00:09:24.825
but you're the one
I think I hurt the most.

118
00:09:24.894 --> 00:09:28.190
The only way I can make it up to you
is to not give you anything.

119
00:09:28.230 --> 00:09:30.494
I knew it.

120
00:09:30.566 --> 00:09:34.096
What I mean by that is that
I'm not giving you anything just yet.

121
00:09:34.136 --> 00:09:36.162
So sit back down there.

122
00:09:38.108 --> 00:09:41.840
I've been thinking about this
for a long time.

123
00:09:41.913 --> 00:09:46.878
How can I give you something and not have it
ruin you like your uncles and aunts?

124
00:09:46.918 --> 00:09:50.012
Even some of their kids.

125
00:09:50.088 --> 00:09:53.353
So I want to give you a gift...
a series of gifts…

126
00:09:53.424 --> 00:09:56.518
leading up to. well…

127
00:09:56.594 --> 00:09:58.624
I wanna call it
“the ultimate gift.”

128
00:09:58.664 --> 00:10:01.360
Now. you fail in anyway.
it's over.

129
00:10:01.433 --> 00:10:03.527
You get nothing.

130
00:10:03.603 --> 00:10:08.165
And everything you do
must be to Mr Hamilton's satisfaction.

131
00:10:10.077 --> 00:10:13.773
You might wanna make friends with him
sooner than later.

132
00:10:14.848 --> 00:10:17.476
This is a voice-activated
Conversay.

133
00:10:17.550 --> 00:10:20.647
It allows two-way communication
between our office and you.

134
00:10:20.688 --> 00:10:24.681
And you can also replay
Red's messages on it if you need to.

135
00:10:24.759 --> 00:10:27.820
- Sir.
- Ah. good.

136
00:10:27.896 --> 00:10:30.392
There's a flight to Houston
tomorrow at 7:00 a. m.

137
00:10:30.432 --> 00:10:33.527
As in morning. 7:00am?

138
00:10:33.603 --> 00:10:35.662
Yes. That 7:00 a. m.

139
00:10:35.738 --> 00:10:39.674
- For what?
- You have until then to accept.

140
00:10:39.742 --> 00:10:42.438
- Why do I have to go?
- You'll find out when you get there.

141
00:10:42.478 --> 00:10:46.346
- This is whacked.
- You might wanna rethink that.

142
00:10:49.853 --> 00:10:53.417
What could he possibly give me
that he hasn't already taken away?

143
00:10:53.457 --> 00:10:56.484
Huh? Screw him.
Screw both of you.

144
00:11:00.498 --> 00:11:03.592
Well.

145
00:11:06.939 --> 00:11:09.840
How was your day?

146
00:11:09.909 --> 00:11:12.606
I'm not sure.

147
00:11:12.679 --> 00:11:15.511
What do you mean?

148
00:11:15.581 --> 00:11:17.943
My grandfather may have
left me something.

149
00:11:17.983 --> 00:11:21.181
- Yeah?
- I'm just trying to figure it out.

150
00:11:21.254 --> 00:11:24.849
- You mean it's not cash?
- I don't know.

151
00:11:24.925 --> 00:11:27.393
Don't know?

152
00:11:27.460 --> 00:11:30.892
If l want to play into his little power trip.
I gotta go pick it up.

153
00:11:30.932 --> 00:11:33.457
- Where?
- Texas.

154
00:11:33.534 --> 00:11:36.766
- Yech.
- You know what? I'm not going.

155
00:11:36.839 --> 00:11:40.570
Well. aren't you
at least curious?

156
00:11:40.642 --> 00:11:43.771
What if it's… gold?

157
00:11:48.283 --> 00:11:50.274
He ruined my life.

158
00:11:50.352 --> 00:11:53.083
My best revenge
is to just…

159
00:11:53.156 --> 00:11:55.090
ignore him.

160
00:11:55.158 --> 00:11:58.560
Besides.
I've got a trust fund.

161
00:11:58.629 --> 00:12:01.401
Worst-case scenario...
I'll live off my mom.

162
00:12:01.999 --> 00:12:03.991
I don't need his money.

163
00:12:04.069 --> 00:12:07.432
Yeah. but one can always use
some extra walking-around money.

164
00:12:07.472 --> 00:12:11.067
Not if I have
to sell my soul.

165
00:12:11.142 --> 00:12:15.273
But. if you had to. at least try to get
as much out of him as you can.

166
00:12:15.313 --> 00:12:19.009
My gosh. What if you actually
had to get a job sometime?

167
00:12:31.899 --> 00:12:34.265
Police escort... sorta.

168
00:12:41.743 --> 00:12:44.269
Uh. ladies and gentlemen…

169
00:12:44.346 --> 00:12:48.009
from the flight deck. we have a very full flight
to Houston this morning.

170
00:12:48.049 --> 00:12:50.314
Uh. excuse me. sir.

171
00:12:50.386 --> 00:12:53.219
Can I- Can I see
your boarding pass again?

172
00:12:55.424 --> 00:12:57.358
Thank you.

173
00:12:57.426 --> 00:12:59.855
Yeah. See. this is. uh...
I'm sorry. This is for coach.

174
00:12:59.895 --> 00:13:01.830
Nah. That's impossible.

175
00:13:01.898 --> 00:13:06.562
- No. It's. uh. 32B.
- Well. change it.

176
00:13:06.636 --> 00:13:09.538
We can't... Please.

177
00:13:09.607 --> 00:13:12.041
We can't... No.
Thanks a lot.

178
00:13:12.109 --> 00:13:14.840
We can't change it.
It's a “Q” fare. You can't upgrade.

179
00:13:14.880 --> 00:13:17.742
- So. can we...
- Do you have any idea who I am?

180
00:13:17.782 --> 00:13:21.616
I- I know exactly
who you are.

181
00:13:21.686 --> 00:13:25.088
You're the guy in Seat 32B. Here we go.

182
00:13:31.464 --> 00:13:34.763
Conversay to Jason Stevens.

183
00:13:34.834 --> 00:13:38.931
Hello. Jason.

184
00:13:39.006 --> 00:13:41.235
What is this. one of those things
Aunt Martha had to wear?

185
00:13:41.275 --> 00:13:44.972
I see you're at the. uh.
Houston airport.

186
00:13:45.045 --> 00:13:46.979
Uh. Baggage Claim.

187
00:13:49.183 --> 00:13:52.949
You got a problem?

188
00:13:53.021 --> 00:13:55.884
You don't look like you've worked
a day in your life.

189
00:13:55.924 --> 00:13:57.915
Great.
The Amazing Kreskin.

190
00:13:57.993 --> 00:14:00.923
I'm don't know what I'm supposed to be doing.
because no one's been...

191
00:14:00.963 --> 00:14:03.830
Hey! Hey!

192
00:14:05.001 --> 00:14:08.368
I'm Gus.
I'm your ride. Get in.

193
00:14:20.183 --> 00:14:22.613
I'm sorry about
your grandfather's passin'.

194
00:14:22.653 --> 00:14:24.653
He and I go way back.

195
00:14:25.056 --> 00:14:28.787
He was some man.
He loved to work.

196
00:14:30.428 --> 00:14:32.589
The man just loved
hard work.

197
00:14:32.663 --> 00:14:35.565
Right. Mind if I smoke?

198
00:14:35.634 --> 00:14:37.898
Ah. it's a free country.

199
00:14:40.373 --> 00:14:42.802
Can you stop
at the next convenience store?

200
00:14:42.842 --> 00:14:45.812
- Convenience store?
- Please.

201
00:14:45.880 --> 00:14:49.246
The last store was
about 50 miles back.

202
00:14:49.315 --> 00:14:53.149
We've been on my property
for the last 30 minutes or so.

203
00:14:57.792 --> 00:14:59.954
Well. seein' as how
you're Red's grandson…

204
00:14:59.994 --> 00:15:03.260
you'll stay in the main house
with us.

205
00:15:03.331 --> 00:15:07.162
I know it ain't much.
The little lady just wanted a modest place.

206
00:15:07.202 --> 00:15:11.196
Dinner's in an hour.
Breakfast at 5:00.

207
00:15:11.274 --> 00:15:13.708
Uh. Gus?

208
00:15:13.776 --> 00:15:17.872
- Aren't you forgetting something?
- I don't think so. Shoot.

209
00:15:17.947 --> 00:15:20.882
The gift.

210
00:15:27.524 --> 00:15:30.049
So this is hell.

211
00:16:09.637 --> 00:16:12.869
Hey. city boy.
Breakfast is over.

212
00:16:12.941 --> 00:16:16.175
Don't you have some kind
of gizmo to wake you up?

213
00:16:16.913 --> 00:16:19.814
Beat it.

214
00:16:32.362 --> 00:16:36.026
- Good morning.
- What is your problem!

215
00:16:47.612 --> 00:16:50.911
Time to get to work.
The sun'll be up soon.

216
00:16:50.983 --> 00:16:55.112
Man Speaking Spanish ]
- Let's go!

217
00:16:57.890 --> 00:16:59.919
Your granddad and I
started out together…

218
00:16:59.959 --> 00:17:02.952
wild cattin' oil wells
down in Louisiana.

219
00:17:03.030 --> 00:17:05.092
Made some money.
We each bought cattle spreads…

220
00:17:05.132 --> 00:17:08.067
as a hedge against
the oil runnin' out.

221
00:17:08.135 --> 00:17:10.262
Of course.
he really made it.

222
00:17:10.337 --> 00:17:14.232
- Nice to own your own little piece of Texas. right?
- Right.

223
00:17:41.271 --> 00:17:43.206
Just from there...

224
00:17:43.274 --> 00:17:45.708
eight feet
from the center.

225
00:17:45.776 --> 00:17:47.767
What?

226
00:17:47.845 --> 00:17:50.644
Lunch will be sent
'round about 11:00.

227
00:17:54.118 --> 00:17:56.147
Well. how far
am I supposed to go?

228
00:17:56.187 --> 00:17:58.121
Don't worry.

229
00:17:58.189 --> 00:18:01.622
You'll run out of posts
before you run out of Texas.

230
00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:05.923
I wish I had a dollar
for every fence post I've ever set.

231
00:18:06.733 --> 00:18:08.667
Matter of fact. I do.

232
00:19:14.507 --> 00:19:16.407
Hey.

233
00:19:19.779 --> 00:19:22.647
What do you think?

234
00:19:29.723 --> 00:19:32.158
No! Hey!

235
00:19:32.226 --> 00:19:36.925
Aw! Come on. man!

236
00:19:37.131 --> 00:19:39.661
So. I'm dying to know. What did you get?

237
00:19:39.701 --> 00:19:42.795
Uh. it's complicated.
but it involves land…

238
00:19:42.871 --> 00:19:45.568
building materials
and slave labor.

239
00:19:45.641 --> 00:19:47.637
They're giving you
a shopping mall?

240
00:19:47.677 --> 00:19:50.339
Not exactly.

241
00:19:50.413 --> 00:19:53.509
So it must be the land. right?
They're giving that to you?

242
00:19:53.549 --> 00:19:57.814
- Uh. land's got a lot to do with it. yeah.
- You don't sound too sure.

243
00:19:57.854 --> 00:20:02.121
Well. whatever it is. I gotta survive
this geriatric cowboy…

244
00:20:02.192 --> 00:20:06.254
until he gives it to me
or when I get back or...

245
00:20:08.767 --> 00:20:10.701
or when I'm finished.

246
00:20:10.769 --> 00:20:12.703
Finish what?

247
00:20:12.771 --> 00:20:15.200
You know what?
Let me get back to you. okay?

248
00:20:15.240 --> 00:20:17.675
Jason. what are you...

249
00:20:18.944 --> 00:20:21.276
So that's it.

250
00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:42.234
Yeah.

251
00:22:07.196 --> 00:22:09.630
Let's go.

252
00:22:09.698 --> 00:22:11.689
I'm not done.

253
00:22:12.936 --> 00:22:14.927
Work's never done
on a ranch.

254
00:23:02.222 --> 00:23:05.954
All right. Whatever. You know. you
do any work like you just did…

255
00:23:06.027 --> 00:23:08.587
You know. you do any work
like you just did…

256
00:23:19.642 --> 00:23:22.271
Now. aren't you
forgettin' something?

257
00:23:22.346 --> 00:23:26.146
- I don't think so. Shoot.
- The gift.

258
00:23:26.216 --> 00:23:29.049
I came here to pick up a gift.
Remember?

259
00:23:35.393 --> 00:23:37.884
That was the gift?

260
00:23:37.962 --> 00:23:40.226
I do manual labor
for a month…

261
00:23:40.298 --> 00:23:44.064
and you're trying to tell me
it was a favor... to me.

262
00:23:44.135 --> 00:23:46.502
- The gift of work.
- Wow.

263
00:23:46.572 --> 00:23:48.904
- Congratulations.
- Look. Hamilton.

264
00:23:48.974 --> 00:23:52.737
Just tell me what
my total inheritance is. I'm over this.

265
00:23:54.514 --> 00:23:57.089
Where are you going?
Where is he going?

266
00:23:57.118 --> 00:23:59.145
Can you tell him
to come back. please?

267
00:23:59.185 --> 00:24:02.177
Mr Hamilton.
Mr Hamilton.

268
00:24:02.255 --> 00:24:04.746
Hey.

269
00:24:04.824 --> 00:24:06.883
Mr Hamilton. sir.
Please.

270
00:24:09.230 --> 00:24:12.995
I think it's only fair I know the amount
of money we're dealing with here. Don't you?

271
00:24:13.035 --> 00:24:14.969
I've been gone for a month.

272
00:24:15.037 --> 00:24:18.234
Just tell me...
What do I have to do? What is it?

273
00:24:18.306 --> 00:24:21.276
Red said.
“a series of gifts.”

274
00:24:21.344 --> 00:24:23.778
But let me add
a personal note.

275
00:24:23.846 --> 00:24:26.713
I. too. think
this is a waste of time.

276
00:24:26.783 --> 00:24:30.480
But it will end shortly.
because you are going to fail.

277
00:24:30.553 --> 00:24:33.681
I expect you to fail
and to fail miserably.

278
00:24:33.756 --> 00:24:35.819
Now. if you do want
to continue…

279
00:24:35.859 --> 00:24:38.433
make an appointment
with Miss Hastings.

280
00:24:40.564 --> 00:24:44.001
Okay. Look. Whoa. whoa. whoa.
Mr Hamilton.

281
00:24:46.571 --> 00:24:50.402
I've been acting like a moron
about this whole thing. and I'm sorry.

282
00:24:50.442 --> 00:24:53.939
And now I- I see exactly
what you and Red have in store for me…

283
00:24:53.979 --> 00:24:56.619
and I think
it's exceedingly beneficial.

284
00:24:57.817 --> 00:24:59.808
So. what's the next gift?

285
00:25:01.554 --> 00:25:03.488
You'll know.

286
00:25:21.275 --> 00:25:23.210
Howdy.

287
00:25:37.259 --> 00:25:40.696
Wait! Wait!

288
00:25:40.764 --> 00:25:43.460
That's an $8.000
paint job!

289
00:25:47.638 --> 00:25:50.234
You don't begin to live
until you've lost everything.

290
00:25:50.274 --> 00:25:52.771
Heck. I've lost everything
three or four times.

291
00:25:52.811 --> 00:25:55.405
It's the perfect place
to start.

292
00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:57.744
Now. for most
of your adult life…

293
00:25:57.816 --> 00:26:00.192
you have been
the life of the party…

294
00:26:00.218 --> 00:26:03.619
and an easy touch
for a lot of weak hangers-on.

295
00:26:03.688 --> 00:26:06.384
Now let's see who
your real friends are.

296
00:26:08.861 --> 00:26:12.525
I was at your funeral. and there wasn't
a single person there…

297
00:26:12.565 --> 00:26:16.897
who wasn't on your payroll or didn't
have something to gain from your death.

298
00:26:16.937 --> 00:26:19.599
What exactly is he
asking me to do?

299
00:26:19.673 --> 00:26:22.973
He wants you to come back
at the end of the month…

300
00:26:23.043 --> 00:26:25.171
with one true friend.

301
00:26:31.820 --> 00:26:35.187
Thank you.

302
00:26:37.226 --> 00:26:41.128
- And how were the lobster tails?
- It was fine. thanks.

303
00:26:41.197 --> 00:26:43.639
The lady was enjoying
the Montrachet.

304
00:26:48.371 --> 00:26:50.601
And sir. the Margaux.

305
00:26:50.674 --> 00:26:52.602
I hope it met
your expectations.

306
00:26:52.642 --> 00:26:54.804
It was terrific.
Thank you.

307
00:26:54.879 --> 00:26:59.544
We don't get too many requests
for the '78.

308
00:26:59.618 --> 00:27:02.653
It's a bit too pricey
for some of our patrons.

309
00:27:06.691 --> 00:27:09.001
I'll just leave this
with you then.

310
00:27:12.931 --> 00:27:16.492
Caitlin. where do you
see our relationship?

311
00:27:17.837 --> 00:27:21.830
- What are you asking me. Jason Stevens?
- Just thinking.

312
00:27:21.908 --> 00:27:24.707
How long have we
been going out?

313
00:27:24.778 --> 00:27:27.542
Uh. an appropriate
amount of time.

314
00:27:27.615 --> 00:27:29.944
- Long enough.
- See? My thoughts exactly.

315
00:27:29.984 --> 00:27:34.614
I was thinking that maybe
it's time to take us… more seriously.

316
00:27:34.688 --> 00:27:36.451
Yes?

317
00:27:36.523 --> 00:27:39.453
But there's something
I want to ask you first.

318
00:27:39.494 --> 00:27:43.358
Jason. if you're talking about a prenup.
isn't that sort of passé?

319
00:27:43.398 --> 00:27:46.095
Well. see. I'm in...
I was thinking...

320
00:27:46.168 --> 00:27:48.500
Excuse me. sir.

321
00:27:48.571 --> 00:27:51.100
The charge card company
declined the charge.

322
00:27:51.140 --> 00:27:54.904
That's impossible. I don't have a credit limit.
Just run it through again.

323
00:27:54.944 --> 00:27:58.403
It's always our practice
to run it through again…

324
00:27:58.482 --> 00:28:00.473
but they declined.

325
00:28:03.220 --> 00:28:05.154
Okay.

326
00:28:05.222 --> 00:28:08.283
So. I was thinking. um…

327
00:28:08.359 --> 00:28:12.523
well. maybe. it'd be a good time
for me to move in with you.

328
00:28:12.597 --> 00:28:16.494
Uh. you move in with me?
Why? Half my wardrobe's at your penthouse.

329
00:28:16.534 --> 00:28:20.399
Just for a change of scenery.
Besides. I'm remodeling my place.

330
00:28:20.439 --> 00:28:24.103
A remodel? But... Who's your designer?
I know everyone in town.

331
00:28:24.143 --> 00:28:27.045
I should've said
I'm beginning to remodel.

332
00:28:27.113 --> 00:28:30.083
I've only really started
with the demolition.

333
00:28:31.385 --> 00:28:34.785
I'm sorry. sir.
Your bank is on the line.

334
00:28:34.854 --> 00:28:36.917
They'd really like
to speak with you. I must insist.

335
00:28:36.957 --> 00:28:39.085
Look. guys. I'm having
a little bit of a setback.

336
00:28:39.125 --> 00:28:42.029
It's nothing that can't be fixed.
All right?

337
00:28:45.232 --> 00:28:49.693
Sweetie. I'm switching accounts right now…

338
00:28:49.771 --> 00:28:52.831
and I'm…
temporarily out of money.

339
00:28:52.908 --> 00:28:55.417
Is there a way
you could pay for this?

340
00:29:01.851 --> 00:29:04.512
Jason. you're. um...

341
00:29:06.155 --> 00:29:08.146
You're. uh…

342
00:29:10.460 --> 00:29:13.055
asking me
to pay the bill?

343
00:29:13.130 --> 00:29:15.963
It's...

344
00:29:24.175 --> 00:29:25.175
You owe me.

345
00:29:26.244 --> 00:29:28.873
What?

346
00:29:28.948 --> 00:29:31.280
Yo. dude.
I'm rollin' over.

347
00:29:31.350 --> 00:29:33.284
What do you mean
I can't?

348
00:29:33.352 --> 00:29:36.788
I have been there for you
countless times.

349
00:29:36.856 --> 00:29:39.118
You owe me. That's it.
Bottom line.

350
00:29:39.158 --> 00:29:41.455
Who was the one who loaned you
10 grand last year?

351
00:29:41.495 --> 00:29:44.091
I could come up with a better excuse
when I was 12 years old.

352
00:29:44.131 --> 00:29:47.194
All I need is a place to sleep.
I don't get what the problem is.

353
00:29:47.234 --> 00:29:49.963
You can let me spend the night.
One night. Hello?

354
00:29:50.003 --> 00:29:52.533
Sorry. Your service has been disconnected.

355
00:29:52.573 --> 00:29:56.071
- Can I help you? Yeah. shut up.
- No. Nothing. thanks.

356
00:30:05.687 --> 00:30:07.621
Jason.

357
00:30:07.689 --> 00:30:09.816
Um... Uh.
what a surprise.

358
00:30:09.892 --> 00:30:14.356
- Mom. you're never gonna believe this.
- I'm afraid I can't let you in.

359
00:30:14.396 --> 00:30:16.793
I'm having a bit of a situation.
I need some help.

360
00:30:16.833 --> 00:30:20.798
- I need to borrow some money.
- Of course you do. Everyone needs money.

361
00:30:23.140 --> 00:30:26.508
Didn't your grandfather
leave you anything?

362
00:30:26.578 --> 00:30:28.874
What are you talking about?
He hated me.

363
00:30:28.914 --> 00:30:30.882
Jason. he did not.

364
00:30:30.949 --> 00:30:35.347
He didn't come around much. but. uh.
I always thought it was because of me.

365
00:30:35.387 --> 00:30:37.549
It doesn't matter.
Do you have any extra spending cash?

366
00:30:37.589 --> 00:30:40.717
I would love
to help you.

367
00:30:40.792 --> 00:30:43.159
- But I can't.
- You can't?

368
00:30:43.229 --> 00:30:46.292
They told me specifically that you would be
comin' around for money…

369
00:30:46.332 --> 00:30:48.361
and that I was not
to give you anything.

370
00:30:48.401 --> 00:30:51.398
But I'm your son. Mom.
That's what you're supposed to do.

371
00:30:51.438 --> 00:30:54.100
If l violate
their instructions…

372
00:30:54.174 --> 00:30:57.541
I am out everything...
everything.

373
00:30:57.611 --> 00:31:00.307
So for the sake
of the greater good…

374
00:31:00.381 --> 00:31:02.815
I must insist
that you leave.

375
00:31:02.884 --> 00:31:04.913
I'm not gonna upset
the whole applecart…

376
00:31:04.953 --> 00:31:07.215
just because you're facing
a few challenges.

377
00:31:07.255 --> 00:31:11.157
I'm sorry. I just
cannot help you.

378
00:31:11.226 --> 00:31:13.491
Thanks.

379
00:31:52.572 --> 00:31:55.014
Hey. man. You're...
You're on my bench.

380
00:31:58.212 --> 00:32:00.203
You're on my bench.

381
00:32:01.615 --> 00:32:03.549
Beat it.

382
00:32:03.617 --> 00:32:07.484
- A simple “no” would have sufficed.
- Fine. No.

383
00:32:07.554 --> 00:32:11.286
- No. what?
- No. you cannot sit on this bench.

384
00:32:11.358 --> 00:32:13.554
This is not your bench.
This is a city bench.

385
00:32:13.594 --> 00:32:16.655
- Go sit on another bench.
- But it's my bench.

386
00:32:16.731 --> 00:32:19.060
I've got just as much
right to it as anybody.

387
00:32:19.100 --> 00:32:21.569
It's a free country. you know.

388
00:32:21.637 --> 00:32:23.599
See. that's where
you're wrong.

389
00:32:23.639 --> 00:32:25.968
Name one thing
in this country that's for free.

390
00:32:26.008 --> 00:32:28.971
You need money for everything.
Without money. you're nothing.

391
00:32:29.011 --> 00:32:31.445
Look at you.
No money. No food.

392
00:32:31.514 --> 00:32:33.510
No family. No friends.
Nothing.

393
00:32:33.550 --> 00:32:36.417
Besides. I'm sitting
on this bench now.

394
00:32:36.486 --> 00:32:38.647
This is my bench.
Okay?

395
00:32:42.059 --> 00:32:44.961
I'll flip you for it.

396
00:32:45.029 --> 00:32:46.997
Fine.

397
00:32:56.742 --> 00:32:59.836
I have a quarter.

398
00:33:01.248 --> 00:33:03.239
Thanks.

399
00:33:12.158 --> 00:33:15.127
Well. aren't you gonna
chase him for it?

400
00:33:15.195 --> 00:33:17.686
Beat it. kid.

401
00:33:17.764 --> 00:33:20.661
I've been watching you.
You're not a real bum.

402
00:33:20.701 --> 00:33:24.229
We saw you at a funeral.
Quite the entrance.

403
00:33:25.941 --> 00:33:29.104
- What were you doing at...
- My mother and I come here for lunch every day.

404
00:33:29.144 --> 00:33:31.941
Except. right now.
she doesn't know where I am.

405
00:33:31.981 --> 00:33:35.212
- Emily!
- Whatever.

406
00:33:35.285 --> 00:33:38.721
Emily!
Oh! Emily.

407
00:33:38.788 --> 00:33:42.385
- You must really be having a bad life.
- Come on. Right now.

408
00:33:42.425 --> 00:33:45.555
I was just having a pleasant conversation
with this gentleman.

409
00:33:45.595 --> 00:33:49.893
- Leave us alone. please.
- Dear. don't be ridiculous. Sorry to disturb you. Come on.

410
00:33:49.933 --> 00:33:52.129
That's okay. I'm not the one
who's disturbed.

411
00:33:52.169 --> 00:33:54.138
Some friend you are.

412
00:33:54.205 --> 00:33:56.139
Thanks a lot. poser.

413
00:33:56.207 --> 00:33:58.370
You know what I've said
about talking to strangers.

414
00:33:58.410 --> 00:34:01.773
- He's not a real bum.
- Hey. Whoa. whoa. Wait. wait. wait.

415
00:34:01.813 --> 00:34:04.677
Okay. this is gonna sound
really. really strange…

416
00:34:04.717 --> 00:34:07.146
but I'm just gonna
come out and say it.

417
00:34:07.186 --> 00:34:09.982
I'll make a deal with you.
I need a friend.

418
00:34:10.022 --> 00:34:12.616
But only for a little while.
and. uh…

419
00:34:12.692 --> 00:34:17.630
in return. I don't know.
I'll take you both to Disneyworld.

420
00:34:17.698 --> 00:34:20.599
Excuse me?

421
00:34:20.667 --> 00:34:24.068
- I need a friend.
- Explain yourself.

422
00:34:24.137 --> 00:34:27.938
- It's complicated.
- No. it's not.

423
00:34:28.009 --> 00:34:30.375
It's pathetic.

424
00:34:30.445 --> 00:34:33.142
- Come on. Now. just because...
- Mom. I told you.

425
00:34:33.182 --> 00:34:36.481
- He's not a real bum.
- Okay.

426
00:34:36.552 --> 00:34:38.987
Oh. dude. come on.

427
00:34:59.210 --> 00:35:02.180
She doesn't even like
Châteauneuf du Pape.

428
00:35:05.384 --> 00:35:09.384
Thank you.

429
00:35:09.654 --> 00:35:12.953
Miss Hastings.
bring me the Stevens file.

430
00:35:13.024 --> 00:35:16.321
Looks like our boy's not even
gonna make it through round two.

431
00:35:16.361 --> 00:35:18.488
But. sir…

432
00:35:18.563 --> 00:35:22.022
doesn't he have until
the end of today?

433
00:35:22.101 --> 00:35:24.035
Well. from what I hear…

434
00:35:24.103 --> 00:35:27.932
he could have another month
and still get the same result.

435
00:35:29.276 --> 00:35:31.335
Yes. sir.

436
00:35:31.412 --> 00:35:35.042
- So. what do you think? Is this a good spot?
- Yeah. perfect.

437
00:35:35.082 --> 00:35:37.679
You can see everything
under the perfect tree.

438
00:35:37.719 --> 00:35:40.382
- Hey! Hey! Give that back!
- I'm sorry. ma'am. I'm just hungry.

439
00:35:40.422 --> 00:35:42.917
- Sir. you need to step back.
- Don't you have a sandwich?

440
00:35:42.957 --> 00:35:44.986
- You need to step back.
- Leave her alone.

441
00:35:45.026 --> 00:35:47.523
Get back! Get back!
I've got 911 all dialed in.

442
00:35:47.563 --> 00:35:49.892
All I have to do is press “Send.”
Sweetheart. get back.

443
00:35:49.932 --> 00:35:53.129
- Ow! No!
- Hey! Hey! Leave 'em alone.

444
00:36:04.047 --> 00:36:07.381
Hoo. hoo. hoo. hoo!

445
00:36:07.452 --> 00:36:09.545
My bench.

446
00:36:14.058 --> 00:36:17.585
- So. you have a bet with a dead guy?
- Mm-hmm.

447
00:36:17.662 --> 00:36:20.597
- Cool.
- Emily. Be polite.

448
00:36:20.665 --> 00:36:24.062
Wait. How can you have a bet with a…
deceased person?

449
00:36:24.102 --> 00:36:26.565
See. that's the part
that's complicated.

450
00:36:26.605 --> 00:36:29.040
So you come up
with a friend.

451
00:36:29.108 --> 00:36:32.168
What do you get if we
go along with this?

452
00:36:32.245 --> 00:36:36.273
- Emily.
- No. it's okay. I don't know.

453
00:36:36.350 --> 00:36:40.150
Something about an ultimate gift
or something.

454
00:36:40.221 --> 00:36:42.248
But you're not sure
what that is.

455
00:36:42.288 --> 00:36:44.586
Yeah. that about
sums it up.

456
00:36:44.657 --> 00:36:47.388
So what do we get
if we agree to do this?

457
00:36:47.461 --> 00:36:51.364
- We need money. How much are you willing to pay?
- Emily!

458
00:36:51.433 --> 00:36:54.869
I'm sorry. You're gonna
have to excuse my daughter.

459
00:36:54.936 --> 00:36:58.373
Sometimes she tends to be
a little outspoken.

460
00:37:02.345 --> 00:37:04.279
I can't promise you anything.

461
00:37:06.949 --> 00:37:08.975
Now. that's better.

462
00:37:09.052 --> 00:37:12.351
But what if
we really did…

463
00:37:14.391 --> 00:37:16.586
become friends?

464
00:37:28.973 --> 00:37:31.408
- Emily. it's not polite...
- Shh.

465
00:37:38.585 --> 00:37:42.920
- So you're Jason's friend?
- Yes. I am.

466
00:37:44.324 --> 00:37:46.918
- True friend?
- Absolutely.

467
00:37:46.993 --> 00:37:48.688
Pinky promise.

468
00:37:48.762 --> 00:37:51.336
So. how long have you
known Mr Stevens?

469
00:37:51.398 --> 00:37:55.301
We go way back.
We're like this.

470
00:37:56.504 --> 00:37:58.495
Now. where do I sign?

471
00:37:59.608 --> 00:38:02.702
And. uh…

472
00:38:02.778 --> 00:38:06.175
he hasn't promised you
any compensation for this friendship?

473
00:38:06.215 --> 00:38:08.206
Look at him.

474
00:38:08.284 --> 00:38:11.515
Does he look like
he has anything to offer?

475
00:38:13.423 --> 00:38:15.549
So. uh…

476
00:38:17.860 --> 00:38:20.795
you expect this friendship
to continue?

477
00:38:20.863 --> 00:38:24.391
I plan on knowing Jason
for the rest of my life.

478
00:38:32.944 --> 00:38:36.376
Tomorrow... lunch at noon.
our usual spot in the park.

479
00:38:36.381 --> 00:38:39.077
Sure.

480
00:38:41.220 --> 00:38:43.188
Just a minute. pal!

481
00:38:43.255 --> 00:38:45.519
You owe me.

482
00:38:52.399 --> 00:38:54.765
Emily. Wait.

483
00:38:56.570 --> 00:38:59.698
They go back a long way. don't they?

484
00:38:59.773 --> 00:39:04.234
There was a time when Mr Hamilton
was quite ill…

485
00:39:04.312 --> 00:39:06.576
and needed
a kidney transplant.

486
00:39:06.648 --> 00:39:11.814
Your grandfather went out of his way
to help him find a donor.

487
00:39:11.887 --> 00:39:14.917
You could even say. I think.
that Mr Hamilton's alive today…

488
00:39:14.957 --> 00:39:16.891
because of Red Stevens.

489
00:39:24.066 --> 00:39:26.429
In the. um. basement
of this building…

490
00:39:26.469 --> 00:39:28.865
there's a small apartment
for a custodian.

491
00:39:28.905 --> 00:39:30.885
It isn't being used right now.

492
00:39:30.907 --> 00:39:33.878
Perhaps you'd. um. like
to take a look at it?

493
00:39:37.849 --> 00:39:39.783
Thank you.

494
00:39:39.851 --> 00:39:43.811
Jason. you have no concept whatsoever
of the value of money.

495
00:39:43.855 --> 00:39:48.622
Money has always been available to you.
like the air you breathe.

496
00:39:48.694 --> 00:39:53.050
I tell you. let's. uh. review some highlights
of your recent past.

497
00:39:55.768 --> 00:40:00.138
A $25.000-per-night suite
in Paris…

498
00:40:00.207 --> 00:40:04.337
with a personal chef
whom you tipped heavily.

499
00:40:04.411 --> 00:40:08.008
Toured the Bordeaux region
in chauffeured hot-air balloons.

500
00:40:08.048 --> 00:40:10.278
That was amazing.

501
00:40:10.350 --> 00:40:12.781
A week of heli-skiing
in Saint Moritz.

502
00:40:12.821 --> 00:40:15.085
A small fleet
of exotic cars.

503
00:40:15.156 --> 00:40:18.455
The latest in everything.
including women.

504
00:40:19.828 --> 00:40:21.955
But the past is the past…

505
00:40:22.030 --> 00:40:25.595
and I figure you've probably had
a pretty tough month.

506
00:40:29.839 --> 00:40:33.104
Well. it's about time.
Thank you very much.

507
00:40:33.175 --> 00:40:35.644
And if l ever
see you two again…

508
00:40:35.712 --> 00:40:37.646
it'll be too soon.

509
00:40:52.063 --> 00:40:54.859
Well. seeing how you've never
held one of those before…

510
00:40:54.899 --> 00:40:56.833
let me explain what it is.

511
00:40:56.901 --> 00:41:00.733
That's a paycheck.
That's for what you earned at Gus's ranch.

512
00:41:00.773 --> 00:41:03.436
Of course. the I. R. S. ravaged it first.
I hate those guys.

513
00:41:03.476 --> 00:41:05.505
In your pocket
every step of the way.

514
00:41:05.545 --> 00:41:08.675
You start out in business.
and then you have to make a payroll.

515
00:41:08.716 --> 00:41:10.745
And just when you think
you're gonna make a...

516
00:41:10.785 --> 00:41:13.481
Mr Stevens. this is
the “Gift of Money.” please.

517
00:41:13.521 --> 00:41:17.047
Yeah. all right. Sorry.
Look at me.

518
00:41:17.123 --> 00:41:22.562
I'm carrying on about death and taxes
even after I'm dead.

519
00:41:22.630 --> 00:41:26.128
Now. you have to take that money and-
as much as you need it yourself...

520
00:41:26.168 --> 00:41:29.626
spend it on someone
experiencing a real problem.

521
00:41:29.704 --> 00:41:31.764
What can they teach you?

522
00:41:31.841 --> 00:41:34.071
Put yourself
in their shoes.

523
00:41:34.143 --> 00:41:37.271
Jason. would you like us
to cash it for you?

524
00:41:37.346 --> 00:41:39.280
Please.

525
00:41:40.349 --> 00:41:42.579
I think we know you
well enough…

526
00:41:42.652 --> 00:41:45.349
that we won't need
any I. D.

527
00:41:45.422 --> 00:41:47.616
How will you know
how I spent it?

528
00:41:50.427 --> 00:41:52.395
We'll know.

529
00:42:01.639 --> 00:42:03.573
Hey.

530
00:42:04.809 --> 00:42:06.744
I didn't
take anything.

531
00:42:06.812 --> 00:42:09.303
Nothin'. Nothin'.

532
00:42:21.828 --> 00:42:23.762
Oh. no.

533
00:42:24.998 --> 00:42:27.728
Great.

534
00:42:56.332 --> 00:42:58.324
Naturally.

535
00:42:58.402 --> 00:43:00.464
A young blonde woman
and her little girl.

536
00:43:00.504 --> 00:43:02.495
- Just down the hall.
- Thanks.

537
00:43:02.573 --> 00:43:04.565
Paging Dr Howard. Dr Howard.

538
00:43:04.643 --> 00:43:07.908
Paging Dr Kline.
Dr Kline.

539
00:43:07.979 --> 00:43:09.970
Paging Dr Howard.

540
00:43:33.073 --> 00:43:35.871
What are you doing here?

541
00:43:38.079 --> 00:43:40.513
- You saw her.
- Yeah.

542
00:43:40.581 --> 00:43:42.412
Did you talk to her?

543
00:43:47.656 --> 00:43:50.428
- So. what's wrong with her?
- That depends.

544
00:43:50.492 --> 00:43:52.670
- On what?
- On who you really are.

545
00:43:54.430 --> 00:43:56.421
Maybe I can help you.

546
00:43:58.100 --> 00:44:00.762
Emily has leukemia.

547
00:44:00.836 --> 00:44:03.700
We thought she was in remission after
her bone marrow transplant…

548
00:44:03.740 --> 00:44:06.710
but a couple of weeks ago...

549
00:44:06.777 --> 00:44:09.549
her body started
to reject the transplant.

550
00:44:12.985 --> 00:44:16.045
I'm sorry.

551
00:44:19.391 --> 00:44:21.324
Uh. hey.

552
00:44:22.560 --> 00:44:25.553
Uh. well. you gotta
need money. right?

553
00:44:25.630 --> 00:44:29.027
Oh. so that's it. You won your bet
with your rich grandfather.

554
00:44:29.067 --> 00:44:31.831
You're back off the streets.
Congratulations. What is it now?

555
00:44:31.871 --> 00:44:34.635
Uh. I do have
to give away some money.

556
00:44:34.707 --> 00:44:38.610
You're getting less mysterious
by the minute.

557
00:44:38.679 --> 00:44:41.542
I bet you're gonna get to the end
of your game. collect your cash…

558
00:44:41.582 --> 00:44:44.111
- and just ride off into the sunset.
- I don't know. Maybe.

559
00:44:44.151 --> 00:44:48.213
But. Alexia. if l can help you.
why won't you just let me?

560
00:44:48.289 --> 00:44:52.418
Because no… rich kid
is gonna use me or my daughter…

561
00:44:52.493 --> 00:44:54.428
to play a game.

562
00:45:06.342 --> 00:45:09.436
She owes $1.600
in back rent. Pay it.

563
00:45:11.415 --> 00:45:16.479
You're a hundred dollars short.
Your check was for 1.500.

564
00:45:16.554 --> 00:45:20.115
Tell Hamilton I'm good for it.
Just pay that bill.

565
00:45:24.862 --> 00:45:29.356
Your other hundred.

566
00:45:29.434 --> 00:45:31.800
Well. push “Play.”

567
00:45:32.003 --> 00:45:35.034
Our lives should be lived
not avoiding problems…

568
00:45:35.074 --> 00:45:39.068
but welcoming them as challenges
that will strengthen us…

569
00:45:39.145 --> 00:45:42.512
so that we can be
victorious in the future.

570
00:45:42.582 --> 00:45:47.648
So. now that I've given you the gift of work
and friends and the value of money…

571
00:45:47.688 --> 00:45:49.717
let's discover
the gift of family.

572
00:45:49.757 --> 00:45:51.748
Now this is a tough one…

573
00:45:51.825 --> 00:45:54.220
but see if it's even
remotely possible…

574
00:45:54.260 --> 00:45:57.124
to get something positive
out of our family.

575
00:45:57.164 --> 00:46:00.596
See if they truly know
how to count their blessings.

576
00:46:01.770 --> 00:46:03.732
I f my doctors
are remotely accurate…

577
00:46:03.772 --> 00:46:06.334
this assignment might even
fall on Thanksgiving.

578
00:46:06.374 --> 00:46:08.866
How appropriate.

579
00:46:08.945 --> 00:46:11.971
He's joking. right?

580
00:46:15.218 --> 00:46:18.381
Dr Allen. you're wanted in O.B.
Dr Allen. please report to Obstetrics.

581
00:46:21.725 --> 00:46:24.819
- Hey. where's the girl?
- Who. Emily?

582
00:46:24.895 --> 00:46:26.829
She's with God.

583
00:46:33.671 --> 00:46:37.072
Oh. there's my best friend.

584
00:46:39.043 --> 00:46:41.238
Listen. about the other day...

585
00:46:43.883 --> 00:46:47.820
So. now you know
all about me.

586
00:46:48.889 --> 00:46:51.790
No more mysteries.

587
00:46:51.858 --> 00:46:55.385
- Look. I'm really sorry.
- Shut up.

588
00:46:55.462 --> 00:46:57.453
Don't be pathetic.

589
00:47:00.267 --> 00:47:02.329
I wonder if he takes
advance orders.

590
00:47:02.369 --> 00:47:05.237
For what?

591
00:47:05.306 --> 00:47:07.831
For my place.

592
00:47:07.909 --> 00:47:10.435
You know. up there.

593
00:47:10.512 --> 00:47:13.413
What do you think
it's gonna be like?

594
00:47:13.482 --> 00:47:15.712
Butterflies.

595
00:47:15.784 --> 00:47:17.912
Lots of butterflies.

596
00:47:18.988 --> 00:47:22.253
Did you know. God…

597
00:47:22.325 --> 00:47:25.690
paints every color on a butterfly
with his fingers.

598
00:47:26.461 --> 00:47:29.630
I didn't know you thought about
stuff like that.

599
00:47:31.134 --> 00:47:34.400
I think about dying.

600
00:47:34.471 --> 00:47:38.339
There's something basically unfair
about a person dying.

601
00:47:40.078 --> 00:47:42.069
I even hate the idea.

602
00:47:47.352 --> 00:47:49.786
You know. I. uh...

603
00:47:49.854 --> 00:47:51.901
I don't know much
about God or...

604
00:47:53.259 --> 00:47:55.920
or Jesus.

605
00:47:55.994 --> 00:47:59.691
But I can promise you that those arms
are meant for you.

606
00:48:04.238 --> 00:48:06.866
What's gonna happen
to my mom?

607
00:48:06.940 --> 00:48:09.184
I really don't hate her.
you know.

608
00:48:24.426 --> 00:48:26.485
Did I mention…

609
00:48:28.964 --> 00:48:31.472
I wouldn't be upset
if you kissed her?

610
00:48:36.373 --> 00:48:38.933
Do you think
your mom and I...

611
00:48:39.009 --> 00:48:41.068
Okay. It's official.

612
00:48:41.144 --> 00:48:44.376
You are the slowest person I have ever met.

613
00:48:44.448 --> 00:48:47.178
You two were made
for each other.

614
00:48:47.251 --> 00:48:49.186
I knew that
back in the park.

615
00:48:49.254 --> 00:48:52.851
- In the park. I looked like a bum.
- Let's not be delusional.

616
00:48:52.891 --> 00:48:55.518
You were a bum.

617
00:48:55.593 --> 00:49:00.691
So. what are you doing
for Thanksgiving?

618
00:49:05.938 --> 00:49:08.600
- Mrs Drummond?
- Yes.

619
00:49:08.675 --> 00:49:12.406
I want to send Emily's charts and blood work
off to a specialist...

620
00:49:12.446 --> 00:49:16.406
see whether or not she's a candidate
for another transplant.

621
00:49:16.950 --> 00:49:21.114
Oh. Uh. will that give her
a better chance than chemo?

622
00:49:23.024 --> 00:49:26.550
Unfortunately. chemotherapy
isn't going to be enough.

623
00:49:28.863 --> 00:49:30.990
I'm sorry.

624
00:49:31.066 --> 00:49:33.000
Thank you.

625
00:50:19.052 --> 00:50:22.784
So when I found out
I was pregnant…

626
00:50:22.857 --> 00:50:26.792
he was getting ready
to leave for college and. uh…

627
00:50:26.860 --> 00:50:29.434
didn't want anything
to get in his way.

628
00:50:31.332 --> 00:50:35.496
And Emily... she's...

629
00:50:38.140 --> 00:50:40.631
she's the best decision
I ever made.

630
00:50:44.914 --> 00:50:48.577
So. apparently…

631
00:50:48.651 --> 00:50:51.643
someone came by
and covered my back rent.

632
00:50:53.623 --> 00:50:56.616
Was it you?

633
00:50:56.693 --> 00:50:58.489
Thank you.

634
00:51:01.899 --> 00:51:05.362
I have a question for you.
and I hope I'm not being out of line here.

635
00:51:05.402 --> 00:51:07.832
I was wondering if you'd like
to join me for Thanksgiving.

636
00:51:07.872 --> 00:51:10.898
Oh. Um. thanks.

637
00:51:10.975 --> 00:51:13.471
That's nice of you to ask.
but I can't.

638
00:51:13.511 --> 00:51:18.381
Um. obviously. Emily needs me here. so...
But thanks.

639
00:51:18.451 --> 00:51:20.479
Well. it's too bad.
because you’re missing out…

640
00:51:20.519 --> 00:51:24.149
on a splendid example
of a way-too-wealthy American…

641
00:51:24.224 --> 00:51:26.522
dysfunctional thing.

642
00:51:26.593 --> 00:51:28.993
- It's... Yeah.
- Oh.

643
00:51:29.062 --> 00:51:33.220
You know. I have the strangest feeling
I might have enjoyed it.

644
00:51:38.872 --> 00:51:41.205
What are you
thinking about?

645
00:51:41.275 --> 00:51:43.209
Nothin'.

646
00:51:43.277 --> 00:51:46.042
You're thinking
about Jason.

647
00:51:57.827 --> 00:51:59.760
Yeah. He's weird. isn't he?

648
00:51:59.828 --> 00:52:01.819
He's a good weird.

649
00:52:03.132 --> 00:52:05.566
You know. he. uh. invited me…

650
00:52:05.635 --> 00:52:08.399
over to Thanksgiving
with his family.

651
00:52:09.807 --> 00:52:13.833
- Oh. really?
- Yeah. Of course. I told him. “Whatever. loser.”

652
00:52:15.580 --> 00:52:19.573
- I think you should go.
- Absolutely not.

653
00:52:22.320 --> 00:52:25.984
I wouldn't dream of missing
Thanksgiving with you.

654
00:52:28.827 --> 00:52:31.091
So why'd you decide to come?

655
00:52:31.162 --> 00:52:35.600
- My daughter banished me.
- Oh.

656
00:52:35.668 --> 00:52:37.933
So I have you by decree.

657
00:52:38.005 --> 00:52:40.565
Mmm. knowing Emily...
by design.

658
00:52:40.641 --> 00:52:42.575
Mission accomplished.

659
00:52:42.643 --> 00:52:44.804
Two completely
opposite people…

660
00:52:44.878 --> 00:52:47.307
who wouldn't have had
a chance without me…

661
00:52:47.347 --> 00:52:49.873
destined to make
each other miserable.

662
00:52:55.691 --> 00:52:58.421
You okay. Jason?

663
00:52:58.494 --> 00:53:01.926
Oh. Don't tell me
you've never been on a bus before.

664
00:53:16.079 --> 00:53:18.014
Wow.

665
00:53:18.082 --> 00:53:20.209
Brace yourself.

666
00:53:20.284 --> 00:53:23.584
Jason. seriously.

667
00:53:23.655 --> 00:53:28.869
- I'm willing to bet that they are perfectly normal people.
- Oh. yeah? How much?

668
00:53:46.914 --> 00:53:49.914
This is nice.

669
00:53:51.986 --> 00:53:53.920
Thank you.

670
00:53:53.988 --> 00:53:58.085
You know. I had my firm
do an informal audit...

671
00:53:58.159 --> 00:54:01.685
just the financials
of the publicly held side.

672
00:54:01.762 --> 00:54:05.591
And there's still
several hundred million floatin' around.

673
00:54:06.468 --> 00:54:08.430
Well. you knew him better than I.

674
00:54:08.470 --> 00:54:11.963
Most of those companies
were privately held.

675
00:54:12.041 --> 00:54:15.271
Maybe we should check into
some of his favorite charities.

676
00:54:15.311 --> 00:54:18.274
- They do have to report large contributions.
- That's a great idea.

677
00:54:18.314 --> 00:54:21.409
Daddy always was a sucker
for a begging hand.

678
00:54:21.485 --> 00:54:26.081
Hmm. Unfortunately.
you're right.

679
00:54:26.156 --> 00:54:30.088
And what sort of business
does your family come from. Alexia?

680
00:54:30.128 --> 00:54:32.995
Um. health care.

681
00:54:33.064 --> 00:54:35.191
Oh. how wonderful.

682
00:54:35.266 --> 00:54:37.795
Well. we have a wing
in the hospital downtown.

683
00:54:37.835 --> 00:54:39.769
A couple of wings. I think.

684
00:54:39.837 --> 00:54:41.799
Or is it
a couple of hospitals?

685
00:54:41.839 --> 00:54:44.274
I always forget.

686
00:54:44.343 --> 00:54:47.072
My daughter is receiving great care
thanks to your father.

687
00:54:47.112 --> 00:54:49.547
Great sector-health care.

688
00:54:49.616 --> 00:54:53.416
Little flat in the third quarter.
but poised to rocket.

689
00:54:53.486 --> 00:54:56.615
Okay. I'd like to propose a toast.

690
00:54:56.691 --> 00:55:00.957
Yes. To each other.

691
00:55:01.028 --> 00:55:05.293
For suffering through a year
of great adjustment.

692
00:55:05.365 --> 00:55:07.459
Uh. excuse me.

693
00:55:07.535 --> 00:55:09.830
Does anyone else seem to notice
it smells a little like...

694
00:55:09.870 --> 00:55:12.396
cowhide in here?

695
00:55:12.474 --> 00:55:17.571
And how are those
sin stocks of yours doing. Jack?

696
00:55:17.646 --> 00:55:20.810
What's wrong with a little
investment in alcohol. tobacco and firearms?

697
00:55:20.850 --> 00:55:26.117
- Over the stench of oil?
- And what's wrong with oil. Thank you very much?

698
00:55:26.189 --> 00:55:29.820
My money's just as
green in Manhattan as anywhere else.

699
00:55:31.762 --> 00:55:36.927
So. who does get
the rest of the estate?

700
00:55:38.268 --> 00:55:40.566
Sarah?

701
00:55:40.637 --> 00:55:44.369
Well. I don't know
anything about that.

702
00:55:44.442 --> 00:55:47.605
Well. you were
the last one in there.

703
00:55:47.679 --> 00:55:51.376
- No. I wasn't.
- Well. that's just ridiculous. darling.

704
00:55:51.449 --> 00:55:53.713
When we left. you were
the only one there.

705
00:55:53.753 --> 00:55:58.521
Well. Jason was also there.

706
00:55:59.893 --> 00:56:02.690
- Ah. Jason.
- Do enlighten us. Jason.

707
00:56:02.762 --> 00:56:04.858
You certainly could not
have been the one…

708
00:56:04.898 --> 00:56:07.472
that received the bulk
of Red's estate.

709
00:56:07.534 --> 00:56:11.898
- Or are you? -Is that why you insisted
we get together for Thanksgiving...

710
00:56:11.938 --> 00:56:15.268
so you could reveal
your newly enhanced trust fund to us?

711
00:56:15.308 --> 00:56:19.807
It's Thanksgiving. I was hoping
maybe we could all go around the table…

712
00:56:19.847 --> 00:56:23.280
and each say something
that we're most thankful for.

713
00:56:27.791 --> 00:56:30.225
- Are you on crack. Jason?
- Again?

714
00:56:32.295 --> 00:56:34.524
Well. here's a thanks.

715
00:56:34.596 --> 00:56:37.926
We don't have to put up with Dad's endless
litany of clichéd quotes this season.

716
00:56:37.966 --> 00:56:40.902
Or hand-spun.
cornpone wisdom.

717
00:56:40.970 --> 00:56:43.970
Hear! Hear!

718
00:56:44.073 --> 00:56:46.474
Who is that?

719
00:56:46.544 --> 00:56:48.606
I think he works
down at the video store.

720
00:56:48.646 --> 00:56:53.141
Well. Jason will tell you
all you need to know about this man…

721
00:56:53.218 --> 00:56:56.654
this… dearly departed.

722
00:56:56.721 --> 00:56:58.717
I mean. he more
than anyone here…

723
00:56:58.757 --> 00:57:01.721
has a bone to pick
with the late. great Red Stevens.

724
00:57:01.761 --> 00:57:05.753
Jason. I can only imagine
what you've just been through.

725
00:57:05.831 --> 00:57:09.829
- I could never get them to be thankful
for anything either. - What have you got?

726
00:57:09.869 --> 00:57:12.047
- Hey!
- What in the world is that?

727
00:57:12.104 --> 00:57:16.439
- All right. give it back.
- Pass it to me. Come on.

728
00:57:16.510 --> 00:57:19.150
- Give it back!
- … and if you do succeed…

729
00:57:19.213 --> 00:57:23.243
- Here take it!
- You'll be one step closer to all I have for you.

730
00:57:23.283 --> 00:57:25.980
What's “all I have for you”?

731
00:57:26.054 --> 00:57:28.583
It's between him and me.
It's none of your business.

732
00:57:28.623 --> 00:57:32.492
It has everything to do with us.
It's our money!

733
00:57:32.561 --> 00:57:35.190
So he's making you work
for your inheritance?

734
00:57:35.230 --> 00:57:38.928
Not anymore. 'cause I don't
think I could ever win at this one.

735
00:57:38.968 --> 00:57:41.493
Alexia. let's go.

736
00:57:42.571 --> 00:57:46.337
- Jason. Wait. Wait!
- Don't!

737
00:57:46.408 --> 00:57:48.438
Just tell them
what they want to hear.

738
00:57:48.478 --> 00:57:50.788
I don't have
to tell them anything.

739
00:57:50.847 --> 00:57:54.178
Jason. you're gonna hear
from my attorney Monday morning.

740
00:57:54.218 --> 00:57:56.482
- Yeah. Ditto.
- Shut up. Jack.

741
00:57:58.723 --> 00:58:00.715
You're all pathetic.

742
00:58:02.694 --> 00:58:05.992
Wait.
Jason. slow down.

743
00:58:06.063 --> 00:58:09.429
I put up with that for years.
I was a part of that.

744
00:58:12.271 --> 00:58:15.240
What happened
to your dad?

745
00:58:15.307 --> 00:58:18.106
He's dead. What else
do you want to know?

746
00:58:19.112 --> 00:58:21.046
How'd he die?

747
00:58:21.114 --> 00:58:25.009
The only person who really knows
just took it to his grave.

748
00:58:25.452 --> 00:58:28.682
Jason. there's something
I always want you to remember. okay?

749
00:58:28.722 --> 00:58:30.985
When I met you.
you were a homeless person.

750
00:58:31.025 --> 00:58:34.359
And you made friends
with my daughter.

751
00:58:34.429 --> 00:58:36.790
We shared
peanut butter-and-jelly sandwiches.

752
00:58:36.830 --> 00:58:40.528
All this without me knowing
anything about your background.

753
00:58:40.568 --> 00:58:45.233
Yeah. well. the problem is.
that's me back there.

754
00:58:45.308 --> 00:58:49.802
Yeah. but you can walk away from all that.
You already have.

755
00:58:49.879 --> 00:58:53.747
I appreciate what you're saying.
but money changes things.

756
00:58:53.816 --> 00:58:58.254
It gets you stuff. It's a- It's a way
to live life worry free.

757
00:58:58.322 --> 00:59:02.283
- Money takes away the worry.
- Yeah. I saw what money can do.

758
00:59:03.594 --> 00:59:05.528
And your worries...

759
00:59:05.596 --> 00:59:08.588
or whatever
you want to call them...

760
00:59:08.666 --> 00:59:10.628
they're not
life or death. Jason.

761
00:59:10.668 --> 00:59:14.565
Okay. I'm sorry. but my getting
my inheritance is a matter of life or death.

762
00:59:14.605 --> 00:59:17.468
And I know when I say that.
I sound like I'm being a Stevens…

763
00:59:17.508 --> 00:59:19.471
and being a Stevens
is all about money.

764
00:59:19.511 --> 00:59:21.445
But it's not.
It's more.

765
00:59:33.961 --> 00:59:37.418
So. I'll pay you back
as soon as possible.

766
00:59:39.399 --> 00:59:41.390
What?

767
00:59:42.903 --> 00:59:45.269
Uh. the money I owe you...
the 1.600.

768
00:59:49.077 --> 00:59:51.068
Happy Thanksgiving.

769
01:00:15.911 --> 01:00:17.903
Marietta Ruby.

770
01:00:20.182 --> 01:00:24.050
From the time I met her
in the seventh grade…

771
01:00:24.119 --> 01:00:26.279
that was my sweetheart.

772
01:00:27.555 --> 01:00:29.602
She didn't
make it easy though.

773
01:00:29.658 --> 01:00:33.054
Took me all the way till the eighth grade
to catch up with her.

774
01:00:33.094 --> 01:00:35.495
She's beautiful.

775
01:00:35.564 --> 01:00:37.497
Yeah.

776
01:00:37.565 --> 01:00:40.762
She passed away
shortly after we were married.

777
01:00:43.371 --> 01:00:45.362
I'm really sorry.

778
01:00:47.874 --> 01:00:50.968
The greatest gift
she gave me…

779
01:00:51.045 --> 01:00:53.911
was the will to move on…

780
01:00:53.980 --> 01:00:55.971
to overcome.

781
01:00:58.719 --> 01:01:01.687
You know. I may have
met someone myself.

782
01:01:01.755 --> 01:01:05.214
Then cherish her.

783
01:01:05.293 --> 01:01:08.692
And become
the man she deserves.

784
01:01:12.364 --> 01:01:14.355
Have a seat.

785
01:01:15.834 --> 01:01:17.768
Now. as I said…

786
01:01:17.836 --> 01:01:21.135
I had a feeling
you were gonna stop by.

787
01:01:24.443 --> 01:01:29.142
That university you attended...
What was it rated? Number three?

788
01:01:29.214 --> 01:01:31.920
Number-three party school
in the country.

789
01:01:32.817 --> 01:01:36.082
Do... Do you truly
knowhow to learn?

790
01:01:36.154 --> 01:01:39.021
Jason. any process
worth going through…

791
01:01:39.090 --> 01:01:42.024
will get tougher
before it gets easier.

792
01:01:42.092 --> 01:01:45.494
That's what makes
learning a gift…

793
01:01:45.563 --> 01:01:47.553
even if pain
is your teacher.

794
01:02:10.319 --> 01:02:12.584
No. There's no way.

795
01:02:12.656 --> 01:02:15.590
Anywhere but there.

796
01:02:15.658 --> 01:02:18.220
I know what he's trying to do.
and it's not gonna work.

797
01:02:18.260 --> 01:02:20.622
He can take his millions
to his grave. I don't care.

798
01:02:20.662 --> 01:02:24.953
What he's trying to do is for your benefit.
not your destruction.

799
01:02:26.002 --> 01:02:28.631
You know. Hamilton.
you sound just like him.

800
01:02:28.671 --> 01:02:31.003
But guess what.
You're not him.

801
01:02:32.074 --> 01:02:34.234
I don't know. son.

802
01:02:34.310 --> 01:02:36.608
I do have one of his kidneys.

803
01:02:39.448 --> 01:02:41.937
He's been out there for hours.

804
01:02:42.016 --> 01:02:44.722
Yep. He's got some big decisions to make.

805
01:02:44.752 --> 01:02:48.188
Do you think he'll
come in or go home?

806
01:02:51.125 --> 01:02:53.116
He doesn't have a home.

807
01:02:53.193 --> 01:02:56.685
You're right! She hates you!

808
01:02:58.066 --> 01:03:01.796
- I know.
- Then why are you here?

809
01:03:01.869 --> 01:03:04.198
I have to leave the country
for a while.

810
01:03:04.238 --> 01:03:06.633
I'm reluctant to go because
of what I'm leaving behind.

811
01:03:06.673 --> 01:03:08.904
What are you leaving behind?

812
01:03:15.248 --> 01:03:18.911
Then you have to go.
Now get out of here.

813
01:03:20.953 --> 01:03:23.016
You screwed up big time.
you know!

814
01:03:23.056 --> 01:03:28.357
I had to eat a rubber hospital
turkey for Thanksgiving!

815
01:03:33.365 --> 01:03:36.801
You better be back
by Christmas!

816
01:04:24.180 --> 01:04:27.706
Even down here. you put your name on everything.

817
01:04:27.783 --> 01:04:30.651
Welcome! Oh. welcome!

818
01:04:30.720 --> 01:04:32.654
Jason Stevens.

819
01:04:32.722 --> 01:04:36.122
Oh! Oh!
So good to meet you.

820
01:04:36.191 --> 01:04:38.284
- I'm Bella.
- Hi.

821
01:04:38.360 --> 01:04:43.178
May I be the first to show you
inside the library your grandfather built?

822
01:04:45.099 --> 01:04:47.033
- Yeah. sure.
- Oh. good. good.

823
01:04:51.105 --> 01:04:53.471
Where are all the books?

824
01:04:53.541 --> 01:04:56.135
Oh.
You joke.

825
01:04:56.210 --> 01:04:58.144
With the people.

826
01:04:59.647 --> 01:05:04.277
Is it not like that in the great libraries
de Los Estados Unidos?

827
01:05:07.654 --> 01:05:10.419
Villagers wait for books.

828
01:05:10.491 --> 01:05:12.481
You bring them new books.

829
01:05:12.559 --> 01:05:17.155
They are waiting for you
to pick up old books.

830
01:05:17.230 --> 01:05:21.188
Exchange. Library. Si?

831
01:05:25.671 --> 01:05:28.936
So basically.
I'm in a third world country…

832
01:05:29.008 --> 01:05:31.476
at a backwards library
with no books.

833
01:05:32.612 --> 01:05:35.714
And the books that are here.
I can't even read.

834
01:05:37.049 --> 01:05:39.041
Great.

835
01:05:53.231 --> 01:05:57.190
This I found
when I was cleaning his desk…

836
01:05:57.268 --> 01:05:59.964
once I heard
of Red's passing.

837
01:06:00.038 --> 01:06:02.613
I thought maybe you
would like to keep.

838
01:06:05.043 --> 01:06:07.169
When you sent this to him…

839
01:06:07.244 --> 01:06:11.010
he proudly showed it
to all of us.

840
01:06:11.081 --> 01:06:13.073
Then the tragedy.

841
01:06:14.717 --> 01:06:16.708
It broke his heart.

842
01:06:21.023 --> 01:06:23.184
Dear Grandpa…

843
01:06:23.259 --> 01:06:25.251
How's Ecuador?

844
01:06:25.329 --> 01:06:27.956
I miss you and Dad so much.

845
01:06:28.030 --> 01:06:30.726
You know. my birthday's
coming up. and I was thinking…

846
01:06:30.766 --> 01:06:33.129
instead of giving me gifts
this year…

847
01:06:33.169 --> 01:06:35.631
could you take me
on one of your trips?

848
01:06:35.671 --> 01:06:38.640
I promise I won't
cause any trouble.

849
01:06:38.708 --> 01:06:41.575
I just want to see you
and Dad again soon.

850
01:06:41.644 --> 01:06:44.771
Write back. please.
Love. Jason.

851
01:07:01.829 --> 01:07:03.797
Hola.

852
01:07:18.945 --> 01:07:20.935
Un momento. por favor.

853
01:07:22.916 --> 01:07:24.975
You look
just like your father.

854
01:07:28.087 --> 01:07:30.021
I was here
the night he died.

855
01:07:36.996 --> 01:07:39.834
It happened up on that mountain.
didn't it?

856
01:07:42.401 --> 01:07:44.448
- Take me there.
- You cannot go.

857
01:07:44.470 --> 01:07:46.431
It is now the province
of the drug lords.

858
01:07:46.471 --> 01:07:48.995
You don't understand.

859
01:07:49.073 --> 01:07:52.976
I'll pay you.
Well. someday.

860
01:07:53.045 --> 01:07:56.808
I understand perfectly.
But. senor. I only have one life.

861
01:07:56.815 --> 01:07:59.579
You're just bargaining now.
aren't you?

862
01:07:59.651 --> 01:08:04.110
Senor Stevens.
you do not want to pay the price it would take.

863
01:08:04.188 --> 01:08:07.181
No one
who goes there returns.

864
01:08:11.329 --> 01:08:17.198
Our guest of honor.
Mr Jason Stevens!

865
01:08:33.650 --> 01:08:36.744
Oh.
Gracias.

866
01:08:36.820 --> 01:08:39.015
I'm afraid to ask.

867
01:08:39.089 --> 01:08:41.579
Oh. you will love it.

868
01:08:41.658 --> 01:08:43.853
It's so rare we catch one.

869
01:08:43.927 --> 01:08:47.952
- The chief is going to talk.
- Oh.

870
01:08:55.837 --> 01:08:58.898
He says we are here
to celebrate you…

871
01:08:58.974 --> 01:09:02.636
and those who keep
the Jay Stevens Library alive.

872
01:09:02.710 --> 01:09:05.179
Oh. no. no. no. no. no. no. no.

873
01:09:05.247 --> 01:09:09.376
No. No. No. no. no.
He must be mistaken.

874
01:09:09.450 --> 01:09:12.413
My grandfather was very generous.
Everything's named after him.

875
01:09:12.453 --> 01:09:17.321
No. it is the Jay Stevens
Memorial Library.

876
01:09:29.403 --> 01:09:31.394
To my father.

877
01:09:31.471 --> 01:09:33.496
- Salud.
- Salud.

878
01:09:39.413 --> 01:09:42.609
Have some more.

879
01:09:44.885 --> 01:09:47.409
- Salud.
- Salud.

880
01:09:47.486 --> 01:09:49.316
Salud!

881
01:09:49.387 --> 01:09:50.946
Salud.

882
01:10:41.137 --> 01:10:43.645
You cannot hope
to find it without me.

883
01:10:44.474 --> 01:10:46.635
How'd you know I'd go?

884
01:10:46.709 --> 01:10:49.506
You are a Stevens.
are you not?

885
01:10:49.578 --> 01:10:52.218
I thought you said
you couldn't take me.

886
01:10:53.783 --> 01:10:57.875
My purpose in coming to you
was a promise I made to Senor Red...

887
01:10:59.489 --> 01:11:01.483
that you could
learn the truth.

888
01:11:01.523 --> 01:11:03.685
He had one desire
and one desire alone...

889
01:11:03.725 --> 01:11:05.659
to ask your forgiveness.

890
01:11:11.700 --> 01:11:14.260
He said one day you would come.

891
01:11:14.336 --> 01:11:16.363
Only then you could
learn the truth.

892
01:11:16.403 --> 01:11:19.201
Stop! Stop the jeep.

893
01:13:10.278 --> 01:13:13.612
He had learned of a village
in the next valley…

894
01:13:13.682 --> 01:13:16.718
that had a plague and needed
medical supplies.

895
01:13:17.786 --> 01:13:20.716
But he never understood
why Red forbid him to go.

896
01:13:20.756 --> 01:13:24.451
There was no plague.
There was no village.

897
01:13:24.524 --> 01:13:27.220
What?

898
01:13:27.294 --> 01:13:30.991
Red wanted to introduce
your father to the oil business.

899
01:13:31.064 --> 01:13:33.828
But your father…

900
01:13:33.900 --> 01:13:36.095
was restless and bored.

901
01:13:36.169 --> 01:13:38.611
- No. No.
- He snuck away. He ran away…

902
01:13:38.639 --> 01:13:41.069
- and took a plane he had no business taking.
- No.

903
01:13:41.109 --> 01:13:45.306
This is what Red wanted
to protect you from. Till now.

904
01:13:45.379 --> 01:13:47.941
There can be no blame
for what happened here.

905
01:13:47.981 --> 01:13:50.710
The penalty for
your father's impulsiveness…

906
01:13:50.750 --> 01:13:52.877
unfortunately. was a life...

907
01:13:52.952 --> 01:13:55.351
his.

908
01:14:12.270 --> 01:14:16.001
Americano?

909
01:15:50.730 --> 01:15:55.928
“It was the best of times.
it was the worst of times…

910
01:15:56.001 --> 01:15:59.301
”it was the age of wisdom…

911
01:15:59.372 --> 01:16:02.169
it was the age
of foolishness.”

912
01:16:05.511 --> 01:16:08.036
Can't you find him?

913
01:16:08.113 --> 01:16:11.708
We think that
he went searching for the crash site…

914
01:16:11.784 --> 01:16:14.150
which is in
lawless territory.

915
01:16:14.219 --> 01:16:17.484
- I'm sorry. Crash site?
- Where his father died.

916
01:16:19.258 --> 01:16:22.625
Well. I mean. is...
is he in any danger?

917
01:16:26.397 --> 01:16:28.331
I'm so sorry.

918
01:16:33.237 --> 01:16:36.262
“Neither love. nor hate thy life;

919
01:16:36.339 --> 01:16:39.776
”but what thou livest.
live well…

920
01:16:39.844 --> 01:16:43.712
however long or short
may the heavens permit.”

921
01:16:49.186 --> 01:16:51.177
Tell me about my father.

922
01:16:52.556 --> 01:16:56.548
In many ways. he was
very similar to you...

923
01:16:56.625 --> 01:17:01.427
restless. rebellious.
angry.

924
01:17:01.498 --> 01:17:04.364
I think Red
saw something in him…

925
01:17:04.433 --> 01:17:08.131
that he didn't see
in his other sons...

926
01:17:08.205 --> 01:17:10.195
a fire.

927
01:17:11.207 --> 01:17:14.870
The same fire
he sees in you.

928
01:17:24.153 --> 01:17:26.143
I still don't forgive you.

929
01:18:05.992 --> 01:18:08.256
Amigo? Amigo.
are you here?

930
01:18:21.173 --> 01:18:24.436
No. no. no! No! No. no!
Please. no! I can- I can pay you!

931
01:18:24.476 --> 01:18:26.636
I have money! Please!

932
01:18:26.710 --> 01:18:30.275
- Oh. God! God! Does anyone
understand what I'm saying?

933
01:19:49.390 --> 01:19:51.381
Death.

934
01:20:57.255 --> 01:20:59.484
Hey. Hey.

935
01:20:59.556 --> 01:21:02.888
Hey. Shh.

936
01:21:02.958 --> 01:21:05.256
Can you walk?

937
01:21:06.328 --> 01:21:08.263
Save yourself.

938
01:21:08.331 --> 01:21:10.264
Not on your life.
Come on.

939
01:21:21.978 --> 01:21:25.947
Come on. Hey. Oh. Mmm.

940
01:22:00.414 --> 01:22:02.405
What are you
doing here?

941
01:22:03.449 --> 01:22:05.441
I was scared to death.

942
01:22:07.254 --> 01:22:09.188
Where's Emily?

943
01:22:09.256 --> 01:22:11.684
Um. she's resting.
She'll see you tomorrow.

944
01:22:11.724 --> 01:22:13.770
You guys have
a good Christmas?

945
01:22:13.793 --> 01:22:16.556
We didn't have one.
How could we?

946
01:22:18.564 --> 01:22:22.729
You know what? We're gonna have
a fantastic one next year.

947
01:22:22.803 --> 01:22:24.793
I promise.

948
01:22:29.543 --> 01:22:31.873
We won't have a next year.

949
01:23:25.294 --> 01:23:30.357
The events of that day
playin my mind over and over and over again.

950
01:23:30.432 --> 01:23:32.195
I'm so sorry.

951
01:23:32.267 --> 01:23:35.600
If your father hadn't died
while working for me...

952
01:23:35.671 --> 01:23:37.633
Please give me
a chance to explain.

953
01:23:37.673 --> 01:23:42.372
Ever since that day. my life
has been filled with grief.

954
01:23:43.778 --> 01:23:46.814
It is apparent that you
will never forgive me.

955
01:23:48.450 --> 01:23:51.043
I do not blame you for this.

956
01:23:51.118 --> 01:23:54.287
It's also something
that I cannot do for myself.

957
01:23:55.324 --> 01:23:58.121
I loved your father
so much.

958
01:23:58.192 --> 01:24:03.390
A parent should never have
a child precede them in death.

959
01:24:03.463 --> 01:24:07.490
It is the most painful
experience imaginable.

960
01:24:11.203 --> 01:24:13.570
that's enough for today.
gentlemen.

961
01:24:30.623 --> 01:24:32.682
Welcome back. stranger.

962
01:24:32.758 --> 01:24:35.454
Hey.

963
01:24:46.038 --> 01:24:47.972
Ta-da.

964
01:24:48.040 --> 01:24:50.031
Here

965
01:24:56.847 --> 01:24:58.873
Wow.

966
01:24:58.950 --> 01:25:01.145
An “airport gift shop” gift.

967
01:25:01.219 --> 01:25:05.177
How thoughtful.

968
01:25:05.255 --> 01:25:07.189
Does it come
with needles?

969
01:25:15.532 --> 01:25:18.728
Yeah. you can kiss me.
even though you're a guy.

970
01:25:23.340 --> 01:25:25.330
I missed you too.

971
01:25:26.877 --> 01:25:29.539
Whatever.
Let's cut to the chase.

972
01:25:30.613 --> 01:25:32.976
You really blew it
with us this Christmas.

973
01:25:33.016 --> 01:25:35.882
I was unavoidably detained.

974
01:25:35.952 --> 01:25:37.885
Okay. yeah.

975
01:25:37.953 --> 01:25:39.944
I want Christmas.

976
01:25:43.192 --> 01:25:45.682
I want to ride a horse.

977
01:25:47.028 --> 01:25:51.021
Oh. I got. like. a week or two
left with this other thing…

978
01:25:51.099 --> 01:25:53.662
but. um. let me make a call
and we'll see...

979
01:25:53.702 --> 01:25:55.694
Jason.

980
01:25:57.272 --> 01:25:59.263
Now.

981
01:26:00.308 --> 01:26:02.208
Okay.

982
01:26:02.410 --> 01:26:06.307
- That works for me.
- Excuse me. sir. It's Jason on line two.

983
01:26:06.347 --> 01:26:08.611
Oh. uh.
will you all excuse me?

984
01:26:08.682 --> 01:26:11.275
I have to take this call.

985
01:26:14.254 --> 01:26:16.518
Go ahead. Jason.

986
01:26:16.590 --> 01:26:19.153
Mr Hamilton. look.
One way or another. this is over.

987
01:26:19.193 --> 01:26:21.155
Either I was in South America
way too long…

988
01:26:21.195 --> 01:26:23.685
or I missed the deadline
or whatever…

989
01:26:23.763 --> 01:26:26.459
but what I'm about to do
is way more important.

990
01:26:26.499 --> 01:26:28.962
And I know you have no reason
whatsoever to trust me…

991
01:26:29.002 --> 01:26:32.768
but I need to borrow
my grandfather's jet.

992
01:26:33.773 --> 01:26:36.708
And I need it now.

993
01:26:36.776 --> 01:26:40.305
I want to take Alexia and Emily to Gus's ranch
for a late Christmas.

994
01:26:40.345 --> 01:26:43.409
Jason. do you know what you're doing?
Look. I have no control...

995
01:26:43.449 --> 01:26:47.612
Uh. what. um. Mr Hamilton
was saying was that. uh…

996
01:26:47.686 --> 01:26:52.487
he'll be sending along
Red's next gift on your Conversay.

997
01:26:52.557 --> 01:26:54.720
You have your bags
packed within the hour…

998
01:26:54.760 --> 01:26:57.751
and. uh. he will
have the jet fueled…

999
01:26:57.829 --> 01:26:59.763
- and ready to go.
- Thank you.

1000
01:26:59.831 --> 01:27:02.766
This means so much to me.
And. Hamilton…

1001
01:27:02.834 --> 01:27:08.246
I promise I'm gonna take back all those
nasty thoughts about you being the Grinch.

1002
01:27:08.305 --> 01:27:11.000
Thanks again. Merry Christmas.

1003
01:27:17.881 --> 01:27:19.815
Hey. Gus!

1004
01:27:22.753 --> 01:27:24.743
What is this?
Snow in Texas?

1005
01:27:24.821 --> 01:27:28.519
Had it trucked in.
Ho. ho. ho!

1006
01:27:30.394 --> 01:27:32.793
All right. Hector. hit it!

1007
01:27:35.999 --> 01:27:38.523
- Merry Christmas.
- Gus. this is Emily.

1008
01:27:38.600 --> 01:27:41.330
- Hi. Emily. Welcome.
- Alexia.

1009
01:27:41.403 --> 01:27:44.270
- Hi.
- Alexia. how ya doin'?

1010
01:27:44.339 --> 01:27:46.432
- And there he is.
- Hey.

1011
01:27:46.508 --> 01:27:49.272
I'll get your bags.

1012
01:28:04.859 --> 01:28:07.919
I see why you chose this place.

1013
01:28:07.995 --> 01:28:10.041
I wish I could take the credit.

1014
01:28:10.098 --> 01:28:13.795
Emily said her wish was to go
horseback riding with you.

1015
01:28:14.569 --> 01:28:16.503
What?

1016
01:28:16.571 --> 01:28:18.800
Emily...

1017
01:28:18.872 --> 01:28:20.863
What? What's wrong?

1018
01:28:23.543 --> 01:28:25.534
She's...

1019
01:28:26.546 --> 01:28:28.844
She's terrified of horses.

1020
01:28:30.851 --> 01:28:32.842
I'm the one who loves horses.

1021
01:28:36.524 --> 01:28:38.513
Oh. Jason. it's so beautiful.

1022
01:28:38.591 --> 01:28:40.582
Thank you.
Thank you.

1023
01:29:03.182 --> 01:29:05.577
Well. this is what I was tellin' you about.

1024
01:29:05.617 --> 01:29:08.278
- Pretty. huh?
- It's beautiful.

1025
01:29:10.255 --> 01:29:12.916
Hey. come here.
I wanna show you something.

1026
01:29:12.956 --> 01:29:14.947
Gonna be okay. sweetie?

1027
01:29:31.941 --> 01:29:33.876
Alexia…

1028
01:29:33.944 --> 01:29:37.606
- there's something I need to do.
- What?

1029
01:29:37.680 --> 01:29:39.614
For Emily.

1030
01:29:45.888 --> 01:29:47.822
And now for me.

1031
01:29:51.526 --> 01:29:53.460
And Gus.

1032
01:29:58.667 --> 01:30:00.601
How about that?

1033
01:30:20.087 --> 01:30:22.917
When I achieved my dreams.
it was like going home…

1034
01:30:22.957 --> 01:30:25.289
to a place
I'd never been before.

1035
01:30:25.359 --> 01:30:27.735
You don't know that feeling.
do you?

1036
01:30:28.662 --> 01:30:31.058
The first few gifts
I've given you have been practical.

1037
01:30:31.098 --> 01:30:35.091
Show up. do this. do that.

1038
01:30:35.169 --> 01:30:39.161
And then the gifts started
needing you to provide input.

1039
01:30:39.239 --> 01:30:41.365
They needed intuition.

1040
01:30:41.440 --> 01:30:44.637
Still. your average person
is too weighted down.

1041
01:30:44.710 --> 01:30:48.841
Jason. you need to be free.
free to dream.

1042
01:30:48.915 --> 01:30:52.782
You need to come up
with a dream. then act on it.

1043
01:30:52.851 --> 01:30:57.152
Jason. this is the time
for you to dream.

1044
01:31:04.863 --> 01:31:07.661
You thinkin' about butterflies?

1045
01:31:07.733 --> 01:31:10.827
No. Jason. I'm looking at the stars.

1046
01:31:10.902 --> 01:31:14.997
You know.
I set this whole thing up…

1047
01:31:15.072 --> 01:31:17.802
because I thought you wanted
to go horseback riding…

1048
01:31:17.842 --> 01:31:19.833
not your mom.

1049
01:31:19.910 --> 01:31:23.402
Get real. Horses are
smelly and sweaty.

1050
01:31:27.284 --> 01:31:30.277
So. sweetie.
what's your dream?

1051
01:31:30.354 --> 01:31:33.346
If you could dream
of anything...anything...

1052
01:31:34.358 --> 01:31:36.383
what would your dream be?

1053
01:31:37.595 --> 01:31:40.427
My dream?

1054
01:31:40.497 --> 01:31:42.863
My dream was
a perfect day.

1055
01:31:44.700 --> 01:31:47.726
And I'm just
finishing it.

1056
01:31:47.803 --> 01:31:52.240
My dream was to be
with people I love…

1057
01:31:52.308 --> 01:31:55.505
who love each other.
that love me.

1058
01:32:11.291 --> 01:32:13.760
What about you. Jason?

1059
01:32:14.762 --> 01:32:16.753
What's your dream?

1060
01:32:19.300 --> 01:32:22.599
I don't know.

1061
01:32:24.272 --> 01:32:28.431
For as long as I can remember.
all I wanted to do was have fun.

1062
01:32:30.311 --> 01:32:32.301
Now I don't have a clue.

1063
01:32:33.747 --> 01:32:36.774
It's okay.
Guys are clueless.

1064
01:32:38.852 --> 01:32:41.513
Hey. you have to know this.

1065
01:32:42.823 --> 01:32:45.017
Even if you don't
have a dream of your own…

1066
01:32:45.057 --> 01:32:46.991
you gave me mine.

1067
01:32:47.059 --> 01:32:49.324
- That counts for something.
- Mmm.

1068
01:32:50.997 --> 01:32:52.987
Of course.

1069
01:32:58.837 --> 01:33:02.137
Look at her.
Isn't she beautiful?

1070
01:33:04.210 --> 01:33:06.983
I mean. except for
her choice in lipstick.

1071
01:33:09.048 --> 01:33:12.949
But you have to admit…

1072
01:33:13.017 --> 01:33:16.646
even if you got nothing
else out of the deal but her…

1073
01:33:16.721 --> 01:33:19.120
you'd still be a huge winner.

1074
01:33:24.396 --> 01:33:28.890
Don't blow it. Knowing you.
you're likely to do it.

1075
01:33:35.073 --> 01:33:37.337
Merry Christmas. Jason.

1076
01:33:44.013 --> 01:33:46.004
Merry Christmas.

1077
01:33:51.754 --> 01:33:54.188
Up until now.
I have only existed.

1078
01:33:55.191 --> 01:33:57.126
I've. um...

1079
01:33:58.494 --> 01:34:00.523
I've drifted through life
day to day…

1080
01:34:00.563 --> 01:34:03.532
thinking that
that was enough.

1081
01:34:03.599 --> 01:34:06.899
And honestly. I don't know
if I have my own dream.

1082
01:34:08.738 --> 01:34:12.566
But I do know I can help
others fulfill theirs. I know it.

1083
01:34:18.113 --> 01:34:21.018
Jason. will you excuse us
for a few minutes?

1084
01:34:22.317 --> 01:34:25.308
Hamilton and Partners.

1085
01:34:33.727 --> 01:34:39.688
We've deliberated and evaluated
whether or not your answer…

1086
01:34:39.767 --> 01:34:44.170
conforms with the expressed
desires of Red Stevens…

1087
01:34:44.238 --> 01:34:48.196
and we find
that your answer does.

1088
01:34:48.274 --> 01:34:53.677
Therefore. we are releasing
an amount allocated for you at this time.

1089
01:34:54.881 --> 01:34:57.850
That is. uh…

1090
01:34:57.917 --> 01:35:03.082
$100 million to do with
whatever you please.

1091
01:35:05.591 --> 01:35:09.688
All of us here at the firm
want to congratulate you. Jason…

1092
01:35:09.762 --> 01:35:11.696
for sticking it out…

1093
01:35:11.764 --> 01:35:14.856
putting up with some
very harsh conditions…

1094
01:35:14.932 --> 01:35:17.367
and prevailing.

1095
01:35:17.436 --> 01:35:19.426
Congratulations. Jason.

1096
01:35:26.110 --> 01:35:28.044
So that's it?

1097
01:35:28.112 --> 01:35:31.477
Yes. I- I think so.

1098
01:35:31.550 --> 01:35:34.712
No. don't get me wrong.
It's not the amount.

1099
01:35:38.855 --> 01:35:40.847
It's. uh...
It's just...

1100
01:35:40.925 --> 01:35:42.950
I don't know.
I was…

1101
01:35:43.027 --> 01:35:45.204
expecting a different
feeling or…

1102
01:35:47.230 --> 01:35:49.221
something.

1103
01:35:51.001 --> 01:35:55.301
I think that's
because now you…

1104
01:35:55.372 --> 01:35:57.306
are a diffferent person.

1105
01:35:59.108 --> 01:36:01.770
And. uh...
And. no…

1106
01:36:01.844 --> 01:36:04.023
we won't cash
that check for you.

1107
01:36:07.483 --> 01:36:10.614
Okay. so he is the best
architect in town. That's great.

1108
01:36:10.654 --> 01:36:13.215
Tell him I want a meeting with him
first thing Monday morning.

1109
01:36:13.255 --> 01:36:16.224
And how much is that?

1110
01:36:16.292 --> 01:36:18.554
I want to tour that property
as soon as possible.

1111
01:36:18.594 --> 01:36:22.857
Oh. that's amazing. We'll have a meeting
at the bank in. let's say. what. a month?

1112
01:36:22.897 --> 01:36:25.359
- That would depend on how
many vehicles you were talking.

1113
01:36:25.399 --> 01:36:27.862
- I'm sorry. Can you hold on?
- Certainly.

1114
01:36:27.902 --> 01:36:31.167
- Yeah?
Mr Stevens. a- a young lady to see you.

1115
01:36:31.239 --> 01:36:33.173
- Great. Send her up.
- Okay.

1116
01:36:33.241 --> 01:36:35.470
- I'm sorry.
- Will it be a large number of...

1117
01:36:35.510 --> 01:36:37.473
Yeah. there are gonna be
plenty of cars.

1118
01:36:37.513 --> 01:36:40.675
- Okay. we'll have to look into it and let you know.
- Okay. thank you.

1119
01:36:40.715 --> 01:36:42.706
You're welcome.

1120
01:36:54.660 --> 01:36:58.290
Oh. I like the remodel.

1121
01:37:00.333 --> 01:37:02.825
Where have you been?

1122
01:37:02.903 --> 01:37:04.894
In and out of prison.

1123
01:37:04.972 --> 01:37:07.804
Mmm.
Good to hear.

1124
01:37:08.874 --> 01:37:11.468
No visible tattoos.

1125
01:37:11.544 --> 01:37:13.637
- I missed you.
- Hmm.

1126
01:37:15.581 --> 01:37:17.693
- What's this?
- Oh. it's nothing.

1127
01:37:18.751 --> 01:37:20.684
That's a nice round number.

1128
01:37:20.752 --> 01:37:24.317
Somehow I don't think you'll be having
any more credit card problems. will you?

1129
01:37:24.357 --> 01:37:27.416
You know. um.
you still owe me a dinner.

1130
01:37:27.492 --> 01:37:29.426
How could I ever forget?

1131
01:37:30.495 --> 01:37:32.485
I missed you.

1132
01:37:36.568 --> 01:37:38.597
I think I still
remember my way around.

1133
01:37:38.637 --> 01:37:41.212
Why don't you meet me
in a few minutes?

1134
01:37:49.480 --> 01:37:51.414
How quaint.

1135
01:37:51.482 --> 01:37:53.472
Hmm.

1136
01:37:57.654 --> 01:37:59.815
Jason?
Where'd you go?

1137
01:38:21.176 --> 01:38:24.577
Shall I keep the limo running.
Mr Stevens?

1138
01:38:24.646 --> 01:38:26.237
Maybe not.

1139
01:38:29.618 --> 01:38:32.948
Ah. Mr Hamilton. Miss Hastings.
I'm so happy you came.

1140
01:38:32.988 --> 01:38:36.515
Jason. what's going on?

1141
01:38:36.591 --> 01:38:38.582
Have a seat.
Please. I insist.

1142
01:38:44.132 --> 01:38:48.553
Thank you all for joining me today.
May I direct your attention to...

1143
01:38:51.572 --> 01:38:53.505
It's called Emily's Home.

1144
01:38:53.573 --> 01:38:57.338
It's for a dozen or more families
experiencing extraordinary health challenges.

1145
01:38:57.378 --> 01:39:02.007
Now. over here
will be the homes.

1146
01:39:02.082 --> 01:39:04.511
They're part of the same complex.
yet individual dwellings.

1147
01:39:04.551 --> 01:39:08.448
Families are gonna be able to live together
while they face their problems.

1148
01:39:08.488 --> 01:39:10.817
Now. obviously. there's
gonna be plenty of parking.

1149
01:39:10.857 --> 01:39:14.387
Over here is gonna be a state-of-the-art
employment center…

1150
01:39:14.427 --> 01:39:17.357
catering to parents. single or married.
who need to earn some sort of income…

1151
01:39:17.397 --> 01:39:19.491
while their child
undergoes treatment.

1152
01:39:19.531 --> 01:39:23.433
Now. at this
state-of-the-art hospital...

1153
01:39:23.502 --> 01:39:27.130
Excuse me.
What's missing?

1154
01:39:27.205 --> 01:39:29.298
Oh. yeah.
A church…

1155
01:39:29.373 --> 01:39:32.104
a worship center.

1156
01:39:32.177 --> 01:39:34.110
How much is this
gonna cost?

1157
01:39:34.178 --> 01:39:37.142
If you look at the prospectus
in front of you. page 5.

1158
01:39:37.182 --> 01:39:40.344
The total initial outlay
will be $350 million.

1159
01:39:40.418 --> 01:39:45.317
Your part will be to underwrite the financing
and a loan guarantee of 250 million.

1160
01:39:45.357 --> 01:39:48.019
I'm gonna be putting up the first
100 million of my own money.

1161
01:39:48.059 --> 01:39:52.889
Mr Stevens. this is all well and fine. We did
business with your grandfather for many years.

1162
01:39:52.929 --> 01:39:57.360
Excuse me. I'm sorry for interrupting.
but I didn't phrase this as a question.

1163
01:39:57.400 --> 01:40:01.732
You are gonna do this. You made this much
off my grandfather in a typical year.

1164
01:40:01.772 --> 01:40:06.232
And. gentlemen. this project has…

1165
01:40:06.309 --> 01:40:09.706
the full resources of the Hamilton
law firm backing it. -Yes? Oh. I...

1166
01:40:09.746 --> 01:40:14.182
Pro bono. as I'm sure
you will be too.

1167
01:40:15.451 --> 01:40:18.281
Wrap up the details for me.
will you. Hamilton?

1168
01:40:18.321 --> 01:40:21.357
- My pleasure.
- Thank you all. I appreciate it.

1169
01:40:27.163 --> 01:40:29.473
Hey! Whoa! Come on. come on.
come on. come on!

1170
01:41:18.545 --> 01:41:20.535
She wanted me to be there.

1171
01:41:22.681 --> 01:41:24.775
It was so important to her.

1172
01:41:27.686 --> 01:41:30.018
She wanted me to be there.

1173
01:42:37.152 --> 01:42:41.486
Jason. Alexia.
as mayor of Charlotte…

1174
01:42:41.556 --> 01:42:45.055
it is my extreme honor
and privilege to preside over…

1175
01:42:45.128 --> 01:42:48.654
the ground breaking
for Emily's Home.

1176
01:42:48.730 --> 01:42:52.460
But it is also a sad day…

1177
01:42:52.533 --> 01:42:58.028
in that the namesake and the inspiration
for this incredible project…

1178
01:42:58.105 --> 01:43:00.629
is not here with us today.

1179
01:43:01.708 --> 01:43:05.076
But her spirit
will always be with us all.

1180
01:43:09.884 --> 01:43:11.875
Jason. Alexia.

1181
01:43:22.429 --> 01:43:24.362
Thank you very much.

1182
01:43:24.430 --> 01:43:28.025
Thanks.

1183
01:43:35.341 --> 01:43:39.004
I am so proud of the man
you've become.

1184
01:43:39.078 --> 01:43:41.773
Thanks in great part to you.

1185
01:43:41.846 --> 01:43:44.843
Meet me at my office as soon
as possible. will you?

1186
01:43:44.883 --> 01:43:48.448
- I have one more matter I need to discuss.
- Of course.

1187
01:43:51.323 --> 01:43:54.852
We understand you went
outside the boundaries of our instructions…

1188
01:43:54.892 --> 01:43:57.622
with one of those gifts.

1189
01:43:57.695 --> 01:43:59.629
What?

1190
01:43:59.697 --> 01:44:02.931
Don't “what” me.
You know what I'm talking about.

1191
01:44:13.144 --> 01:44:17.765
- Miss Hastings. will you. uh. dismiss everyone. please?
- Oh. Yes. sir.

1192
01:44:36.132 --> 01:44:38.498
Over the course of several days…

1193
01:44:38.567 --> 01:44:40.997
this investigator personally witnessed
and recorded the subject…

1194
01:44:41.037 --> 01:44:46.119
as he committed various misdemeanor
infractions for which he was never cited.

1195
01:44:48.743 --> 01:44:52.305
Nevertheless. illegal
activities did occur.

1196
01:44:53.382 --> 01:44:56.645
Panhandling.
bordering on assault…

1197
01:44:59.754 --> 01:45:04.088
stealing private property.
resale of stolen items…

1198
01:45:08.095 --> 01:45:11.826
street vending
without a permit…

1199
01:45:11.899 --> 01:45:13.832
jaywalking.

1200
01:45:13.900 --> 01:45:18.465
It is the opinion of this investigator
that the subject is a reprobate…

1201
01:45:18.505 --> 01:45:22.336
and not capable of completing
the 12 gifts laid out in Red Stevens's will.

1202
01:45:22.376 --> 01:45:24.171
That's enough. Miss Hastings.

1203
01:45:24.211 --> 01:45:26.406
My pleasure. Mr Hamilton.

1204
01:45:27.413 --> 01:45:32.316
Jason. if you made it this far.
he had one final message.

1205
01:45:50.069 --> 01:45:52.401
- Jason.
- Yeah?

1206
01:45:54.206 --> 01:45:56.977
You gave away the $100 million?
All of it?

1207
01:45:58.943 --> 01:46:02.006
- Yeah. so what?
- Well. if you're standing here now…

1208
01:46:02.046 --> 01:46:07.177
it means that not only have you succeeded
in receiving all of my gifts…

1209
01:46:07.251 --> 01:46:10.881
but have done so beyond
the boundaries that I have set.

1210
01:46:12.524 --> 01:46:16.050
I guess that means
that I have succeeded as well.

1211
01:46:18.262 --> 01:46:20.889
What I could not
accomplish in life…

1212
01:46:20.964 --> 01:46:23.229
I have done in death.

1213
01:46:24.668 --> 01:46:29.434
As long as you are
still alive. I will be too.

1214
01:46:32.709 --> 01:46:34.700
I love you. Son.

1215
01:46:34.777 --> 01:46:36.608
I love you too.

1216
01:46:39.983 --> 01:46:42.041
Good-bye. Jason.

1217
01:47:31.297 --> 01:47:34.425
“As executor of the estate
of Red Stevens…

1218
01:47:34.500 --> 01:47:37.074
”I hereby execute
and otherwise assign…

1219
01:47:37.136 --> 01:47:41.800
”complete and controlling
interest to Jason Stevens…

1220
01:47:41.874 --> 01:47:44.173
”the balance of Red's estate…

1221
01:47:45.512 --> 01:47:48.742
”including all holdings.
investment portfolio…

1222
01:47:48.814 --> 01:47:52.375
”and offshore interests…

1223
01:47:52.451 --> 01:47:57.581
totaling in excess
of two billion dollars.”

1224
01:47:59.424 --> 01:48:04.123
Depending on OPEC prices
and foreign currency fluctuations. of course.

1225
01:48:17.608 --> 01:48:20.238
I need a lawyer for a few business ideas I have…

1226
01:48:20.278 --> 01:48:22.239
a few still
in the dream stage.

1227
01:48:22.279 --> 01:48:24.214
When would you like to meet?

1228
01:48:24.282 --> 01:48:26.512
Meet? Hell. you're hired.

1229
01:48:26.584 --> 01:48:29.546
Sir. are you sure you wouldn't like to meet first?

1230
01:48:29.586 --> 01:48:33.078
You were at the top
of your law class. were you not?

1231
01:48:33.156 --> 01:48:35.419
- Yes. sir.
- Then you're my lawyer.

1232
01:48:35.491 --> 01:48:38.923
Now let's get on with it.
We got a world to conquer.

1233
01:48:50.273 --> 01:48:53.732
Do you think I'm old.
Miss Hastings?

1234
01:48:53.810 --> 01:48:55.868
Mm-mmm.

1235
01:48:55.945 --> 01:49:01.074
Well. I think it's about time I retire
from this law firm.

1236
01:49:03.918 --> 01:49:07.217
Whatever will you do.
Mr Hamilton?

1237
01:49:09.457 --> 01:49:11.618
Go to work
with Jason Stevens.

1238
01:49:14.228 --> 01:49:16.254
- Change the world.
- Mmm.

1239
01:49:21.402 --> 01:49:25.404
Hi.

1240
01:49:41.888 --> 01:49:43.879
Thank you.

1241
01:50:18.557 --> 01:50:21.354
So I want
to give you a gift...

1242
01:50:21.425 --> 01:50:26.454
a series of gifts
leading up to. well…

1243
01:50:26.531 --> 01:50:29.328
I wanna call it
“the ultimate gift.”

1244
01:50:29.400 --> 01:50:32.831
Now. you fail in anyway.
it's over. You get nothing.

1245
01:50:38.942 --> 01:50:42.173
You know. you do any work
like you just did…

1246
01:50:42.245 --> 01:50:44.179
you can do anything.

1247
01:50:56.225 --> 01:50:58.990
Now. aren't you
forgettin' something?

1248
01:50:59.062 --> 01:51:02.325
- I don't think so. Shoot.
- The gift.

1249
01:51:02.397 --> 01:51:04.195
The gift of work.

1250
01:51:04.266 --> 01:51:06.826
- Wow.
- Congratulations.

1251
01:51:12.841 --> 01:51:16.173
The charge card company
declined the charge.

1252
01:51:16.244 --> 01:51:19.374
That's impossible. I don't have a credit limit.
Just run it through again.

1253
01:51:19.414 --> 01:51:24.818
It's always our practice to run it
through again. but they declined.

1254
01:51:31.858 --> 01:51:33.554
I need a friend.

1255
01:51:33.628 --> 01:51:37.028
You expect this friendship
to continue?

1256
01:51:37.097 --> 01:51:40.533
I plan on knowing Jason
for the rest of my life.

1257
01:51:47.374 --> 01:51:50.832
Do... Do you truly
know how to learn?

1258
01:51:51.912 --> 01:51:55.039
Villagers wait for books.

1259
01:51:55.114 --> 01:51:57.049
You bring them new books.

1260
01:51:57.117 --> 01:52:01.678
They are waiting for you
to pick up old books.

1261
01:52:01.754 --> 01:52:05.154
Exchange. Library.
Si?

1262
01:52:17.502 --> 01:52:20.866
Well. you don't begin to live
until you've lost everything.

1263
01:52:20.906 --> 01:52:24.363
Wait! Wait!

1264
01:52:24.442 --> 01:52:28.070
That's an $8.000 paint job!

1265
01:52:28.145 --> 01:52:30.375
Heck. I've lost everything
three or four times.

1266
01:52:30.415 --> 01:52:32.678
It's the perfect
place to start.

1267
01:52:40.491 --> 01:52:44.860
And Emily... she's...

1268
01:52:47.331 --> 01:52:50.128
- she's the best decision I ever made.
- **

1269
01:52:51.200 --> 01:52:54.261
What's gonna
happen to my mom?

1270
01:52:54.338 --> 01:52:56.582
I really don't hate her.
you know.

1271
01:53:08.783 --> 01:53:11.274
- Salud.
- Salud.

1272
01:53:11.353 --> 01:53:13.218
Salud!

1273
01:53:13.288 --> 01:53:15.721
Salud.

1274
01:53:25.600 --> 01:53:30.560
Jason. you need to be free.
free to dream.

1275
01:53:30.639 --> 01:53:33.667
You need to come up
with a dream. then act on it.

1276
01:53:33.707 --> 01:53:37.007
And honestly. I don't know
if I have my own dream.

1277
01:53:38.912 --> 01:53:42.015
But I do know I can help others
fulfill theirs.

1278
01:53:47.354 --> 01:53:50.083
Uh. I do have to
give away some money.

1279
01:53:50.156 --> 01:53:53.127
You're getting
less mysterious by the minute.

1280
01:53:54.828 --> 01:53:56.988
She owes $1.600
in back rent.

1281
01:53:57.063 --> 01:53:59.156
Pay it.

1282
01:53:59.232 --> 01:54:01.359
You're a hundred
dollars short.

1283
01:54:11.109 --> 01:54:13.670
So. apparently…

1284
01:54:14.747 --> 01:54:17.681
someone came by
and covered my back rent.

1285
01:54:18.684 --> 01:54:20.675
Was it you?

1286
01:54:22.687 --> 01:54:24.484
Thank you.

1287
01:54:32.631 --> 01:54:34.621
What would
your dream be?

1288
01:54:36.032 --> 01:54:38.831
My dream?

1289
01:54:38.903 --> 01:54:40.871
My dream was
a perfect day.

1290
01:54:47.677 --> 01:54:50.043
And I'm just
finishing it.

1291
01:54:58.822 --> 01:55:01.985
- I love you. Son.
- I love you too.

1292
01:55:05.128 --> 01:55:07.391
Good-bye. Jason.
